ascents.name: Paint it Black
ascents.comment: Really cool to get on a hard climb that is also high quality. 4 sessions, first two were basically figuring out the second move aka my crux. Had a ton of support from the homies and tried hard, psyched to get it done before the heat comes. Out of my depth in this grade range so I’m going with consensus.

ascents.name: Mind to Motion
ascents.comment: Cool resistance climb. No hard moves, actually not too hard to put together either... came to it fresh 3rd sesh and bagged it first go from the start. Just had to stop being stupid and forgetting where to put my foot for the heel hook at the crux. Guess I'll take the points but it's questionable, slasher for sure.

ascents.name: Warrior Up
ascents.comment: Hardest move I've done. Meaningful to send a condensed difficult boulder. Tried once last season, felt impossible, but did it in a session this year. Yahtzee!

ascents.name: Dark Waters Low
ascents.comment: 7 or 8 sessions, and a lot more effort than I was expecting for the training project. Felt easy today, sent first go of the session. Still way harder than wheel. Happy to be done with the cave, although there's always another stupid contrivance to do in there...

ascents.name: The wheel of wolvo
ascents.comment: 3 sessions, sent just before the rain with the parents supporting (no idea why they were psyched to come down to lincoln...). Cool moves, very reachy, super resistant. Always wanted to climb V15 maybe some day, feels like 12/13 into 10/11, but I do think I finally deserve soft 14. Couple minor dabs but nothing big enough to bother me (sorry Liam), psyched to be pushing through into some harder stuff! LETS GOOOOO!!!

ascents.name: Masterpiece
ascents.comment: Very soft but I'll take it. Top is still pretty scary due to the rapidly decreasing rock quality the higher you go. Super fun moves, super fun problem. Thanks to Dor Tim and Jess for hiking up the hill to get me on this thing!

ascents.name: Riverbed
ascents.comment: Ups and downs with this one, really cool problem but the crux for me was sliding off the abnormally slick tampered right hand hold. Came back again and had the same issue, but first go on the cleanup day just overpowered it and it felt easy. Whatever it's a cool climb, I just wish it hadn't been messed with.

ascents.name: Bear Toss
ascents.comment: Cool down project goes down! 8C and 8B in a day, but most notably I flashed Bulgin out. Won't have another opportunity for the 15 factorial any time soon, too bad I squandered it.

ascents.name: The Right
ascents.comment: Mega softy, could be a slasher. Almost bagged it in a sesh right after doing it via freedom, but fell off the last move 3 times. Came back for the quick takedown, but not before watching Conor take the worst fall possible. Jeebus.

ascents.name: Kook slams (Boulder Portion)
ascents.comment: Took a few sessions of being very close to sending to figure out all the micro beta I needed. Never felt much pressure to send considering I'll come back every day its snowing, but still happy to finish it off. Wild moves I'll probably never do on another boulder. I'd feel bad about dropping off of this one if most every sport climb wasn't just a dropoff someone decided to put chains at.

ascents.name: Pocket Frogs
ascents.comment: Took a while. Don't like finger pockets, even super natural ones. Really good movement though, Mark fired it real quick!

ascents.name: Circadian Rhythm
ascents.comment: Changed my beta 4 times to try to avoid the dab but not make it impossible, finally figured it out and it came together. Incredible climb minus the start. Bryce almost had it 3 days on... he'll be back

ascents.name: The third wheel
ascents.comment: No hard moves and not really power endurance so I'm unsure of what makes this difficult. Probably nothing. Linked it up, directo on Aint no heaven is pretty hard.

ascents.name: Nothing else matters
ascents.comment: Came for the camaraderie, stayed for the morpho contrivances. Pretty hard, but did it in a session plus one for Mind, so can't be too tough.

ascents.name: Top Notch
ascents.comment: Life lister down! That movement and rock quality tho... Tito classic and well worth the hype. Stuck the first move second go, then flailed for a bit, but Liam hiking it inspired me to pull it off a few tries later. Almost fell on an unnecessary move I added would have been shameful. Fortunately didn't. YES!

ascents.name: The Wheel of Chaos
ascents.comment: Not quite as sick as the direct, and felt not quite as hard either... 3rd session counting direct sessions, but second go from the start. Too many easy moves to be 14 for me, prob more like 5.12d ;) For sure a step under the Wheel of Wolvo. I have endurance!

ascents.name: The Wheel Direct
ascents.comment: This is the best looking line on the boulder! From way down in the hole straight out. Long and resistancy, but the only hard move is on Katana... Almost flashed to the jugs, had to return for a second session though and almost didn't send after a tragic punty foot pick at the very end on my first go. Second go of the day chicken winged it out but only barely...

ascents.name: Vanilla Sky
ascents.comment: After work sesh it goes! Tried so effing hard. 3 Sessions, ended up having to use the closest worst part of the crimp to get my wrist at the right angle. 6 foot span on me, with a few more inches prob V10 or 11, with less prob much harder. Double clutch method is ludicrous.

ascents.name: Wanderlust
ascents.comment: Could be 12, felt easy and did it in a session but I also fell off the end once and almost pumped out on the send. Trickier and longer than it is physical and difficult. Used a different sequence it sounds like, but everyone has probably used a different sequence there's so many holds. Chris was here today!

ascents.name: Free Range (aka Cage Free Assis)
ascents.comment: Wow happened a lot sooner than expected. Couple terrible sessions on it led to a fluke link to the last move 4 months ago. Turns out wasn't a fluke, dialed in the intro and fired in the snow. Doesn't everyone send this  one while it's snowing?

ascents.name: Calm Ethereal
ascents.comment: 2nd day takedown, way too tired last time to have a shot. Striking line, good rock, cool movement even though it hurts my wrist. Had to take the pants off that's how you know it's getting serious. Best hard one I've climbed in a good while.

ascents.name: Muddy Waters Low
ascents.comment: Right after Dark Waters Low. Felt to be in good shape today. Bonus fitness for the session woohoo

ascents.name: Dark Waters
ascents.comment: Thought I was fat 5 months ago when I last tried this, turns out it is actually hard for me. Close compression underclings... low end for sure even for me though.

ascents.name: Things done changed
ascents.comment: 6 sessions. I don't always upgrade, but when I do I earn it. Heinous for me, probably the hardest boulder I have sent to date.

ascents.name: The Automator
ascents.comment: Crux is pulling the last sort of hard move after holding a 90 degree bent arm hang on crimps for a minute to keep your ass from touching the ground. Icing on the cake is the hole in my finger, but at least I didn't circumcise it, and I am actually happy because this one was hard for me and took a few days and now I never need to climb on it again. Plus it's classic so you gotta...

ascents.name: Nuthin but sunshine
ascents.comment: Surprise send. Pretty hot had to try hard and ended up a bit desperate. I'm sure it's easier when it's cold...

ascents.name: The Great War for Civilisation
ascents.comment: Glad I could do the better line. Climbed poorly and had to try harder to make up for it. Great war for civilized asians!

ascents.name: The Mote in God's Eye
ascents.comment: Super cool feature climbing with weird moves and a full value topout. Sick! One sesh to suss, and a night sesh with will and Zach to take it down.

ascents.name: Clan of the Cave Bears
ascents.comment: First session I was ready to bunker down for a 10+ session epic, felt impossible. Second session felt the same until a few beta tweaks and some inexplicable heel stickiness just made it happen out of thin air. I am very fucking surprised.

ascents.name: Barrel Rider
ascents.comment: My name is Faniel Dong and Barrel Rider V13 is the best hard boulder I've done so far in Colorado. Sent at the end of 2 very long sessions, fell off the end more times than I'd care to admit. So soft.

ascents.name: Faline (AKA Bambi's Fantasy)
ascents.comment: Just another stupid and hard link up done by a bored person who lives too close to the crag. Maybe someone else has done this and not claimed it because its stupid. Maybe not. A few hard moves from Bambi links into the stand of Fantasia. For sure harder than Fantasia, intro boulder is a grade or two harder. Someone else come do this stupid contrivance and tell me how hard it is, am I selling it yet? One more way harder line in the cave left... I guess I'm still on the team!

ascents.name: Fantasia
ascents.comment: Got to the pocket move twice first day attempting, then went on to continue to fall there for 4 days including once after sticking the pocket and once off the slab. Then I broke the huge foot in the middle section, but other beta works fine. Once I got my new intro sequence dialed felt like V10/11 into the stand which I guess is 11/12. Hardest I've worked for a boulder in a while, can't really grade something like this.

ascents.name: The Swarm Direct
ascents.comment: Easier than the swarm. a couple tries, think I've got that move on lock now. MARK!!!!!!

ascents.name: Mandala sds
ascents.comment: Wanted to do this ever since I saw the video of Mark sahting his way up this testpiece. Sent first try 2nd session this year after punting the previous time. Psyched to finish this iconic prow!

ascents.name: The Abattoir
ascents.comment: Wow. Was not expecting to do this anytime soon, but psyched I did! Couple sessions to get to the last move, couple more to stick the last move and then send. Pure, and just as challenging technically as it is physically. Topout was wet took me 15 minutes to get down. Carlo and Mark's back to back comments are gold.

ascents.name: Roses and Blue Jays
ascents.comment: This is a pretty amazing line. Had to alter the trip plan a bit to improve my chances of sending and it paid off. Perfect last move! So fun.  The gloves are now OFF!

ascents.name: Vice president
ascents.comment: Harder than the Vice but still soft. Really wanted to DG, thought it would be easy when I did the crux static in Iso, turns out it's harder from the start... glad Bryce viced today I never want to come back up here.

ascents.name: Madiba
ascents.comment: Sent fast in a session, very uncertain of the grade... Hardest move for me was definitely getting to the peanut. Could be V12 for sure but I'm going to #keeprocklandssoft on this one. Amazing movement testpiece!

ascents.name: Amandla
ascents.comment: Felt hard until everything clicked 4th session and it felt leagues easier. Such a good problem that was definitely high on the list ever since I've gotten here, and I thought I might not pull off.

ascents.name: The Vice
ascents.comment: 3 sessions, kind of epic for me. Thought I would be much less psyched on this because it's lowball and long but it looks good in person and is soft so problems solved. I can't pinch and have poor power endurance so this must be quite soft. Bryce almost followed, and death screamed all the way onto the ground. Vice president is definitely the obvious better line. Start of an epic day!

ascents.name: The power of one
ascents.comment: 2 sessions with OG ish shoulder beta. Not too hard, but definitely a bit techy at the top. Bryce came up HUGE with a send of this after being basically dead from too much climbing. BIG DAY for the Yatta Boyz.

ascents.name: Mooiste Meisie
ascents.comment: Such a fun core tensiony boulder! Punted 3rd or 4th go at the end and got flash pumped, then pulled a send out of my ass to maintain the 8B in less than 10 tries streak! Surely this can't continue, but for now I feel like Midas, except instead of gold everything I touch turns to soft.

ascents.name: King of Limbs
ascents.comment: Felt really really hard but took me less than 10 tries so it must be soft. Executed perfectly on my last go of the day and it came together! Climbing 13s in a session... this is what Rocklands is all about!

ascents.name: Quintessential
ascents.comment: Less than 10 tries. Fired it right after Dan, sharp and aggressive! Psyched to get a hard one done this early in the trip. Quintessential rounds out the quintuple double for the day!

ascents.name: Slasher
ascents.comment: First came up here with Bryce a year and a half ago, and couldn't do any of the moves. Wouldn't have come back to it if he wasn't so psyched, but slowly it came together. Watching him send got me amped to get it done, and even though I missed the send train I managed to Yatta it on my 4th session. So satisfying to hit the lip!

ascents.name: Blackout
ascents.comment: 1st go, 3rd session in standard fashion. Then Bryce smashed his mega proj and I almost followed him up it. Nothing will ever be as easy as straight down pulling on crimps for me. Good thing Isamer left or I wouldn't have sent. Mega soft for me. Yatta!

ascents.name: DIRECTION
ascents.comment: Stage 2 warm up for swarm. If t bird is 11, this is 13, albeit low end. Hardest move for me is the easiest move for everyone else, only fell once on the t bird move. Best contrived dropoff I've climbed in a while.

ascents.name: The Swarm
ascents.comment: Psyched to finish this thing after punting off the last move in my first session. Thought for a moment I was going to take it to the top on the flash go after sticking the first 3 moves, but the shoulder move is still hard! Ended up sending first go of the 3rd session. Glad practicing all those ling drive by's finally paid off. Shout out to Jess and all the people who hiked/sledded out to support me!

ascents.name: Black #1
ascents.comment: Thought it was impossible but actually it's just soft. Just had to bump left hand. Topout is a bit spicy... 2 new problems in Joe's in a day? Unheard of.

ascents.name: Atrésie assis
ascents.comment: Spent the first half of the day unsuccessfully working on logistics for my rental car, spent the second half going to two areas with moist boulders to no avail. Finally bailed to my go to backup Rempart around 6PM. Came to this looking for a workout, all I left with was 12 easy points.

ascents.name: Gourmandise raccourci
ascents.comment: Chalk really disappears off my hands quickly these days. Still did it quick, why is 8a+ easier than 7C+ here.

ascents.name: Gecko
ascents.comment: Awesome, really wanted to do this one. Felt similar to karma, took an hour or two. Maybe  I'll be back...

ascents.name: Karma
ascents.comment: Feeling cute may dg later. Don't have enough to go off of here yet, we'll see after I try some more 8s. Super psyched to bag this thing, incredible line I've always heard so much about. Did it in about an hour.

ascents.name: Electroboogie
ascents.comment: Really hard to grade this one... Almost did it in a session but didn't switch to the compression method until halfway through... then fell off the end for 2 more sessions because conditions didn't feel good, then finally bagged it and it felt so easy. Idk. Very cool sloper pinch though.

ascents.name: The bizarre Ride
ascents.comment: Broke the left hand hold at the crux on the flash go, but probably wasn't going to flash it anyways. Still goes, did it a few desperate goes later. Woohoo dropoffs

ascents.name: *Unendliche Geschichte 1
ascents.comment: Could be 8a eff if I know. Had two heel slips at the start then cruised the rest of it. Perhaps I will throw myself at the link...

ascents.name: *Voigas
ascents.comment: Kinda hard for me, had a mini epic but somehow prevailed in the end. Ouch my pecs.

ascents.name: Mini compressor
ascents.comment: Few goes, was two moves in when I heard someone say "Come on Bryce" and I was like oh shit don't drop the ball now. Simul send, somehow Bryce managed crazy footstab cut beta on Free Basin. Legendary.

ascents.name: Low Left Veritas
ascents.comment: I'm going to savor doing these piles one at a time, very slowly. Dropped off the lip twice last time cuz I was pumped and didn't want to sacrifice my alpine season, priorities.

ascents.name: The Right (via Freedom)
ascents.comment: Very cool line, bit of a razor on the left pinky though. Sent in a few goes, didn't know we were giving highball grades to 15 foot tall problems these days.

ascents.name: Carefully by Hand
ascents.comment: Harder than it looks. Also worse than it looks which is remarkable all things considering.

ascents.name: The Wheel of Fortune
ascents.comment: Feels like V6 into V11, but then it's kinda hard so dunno 12 seems fair. Couldn't fit the kneebar after I chossed off a bunch of rock trying to find one that would fit, but it's not really necessary anyways. After work sesh with Andy, tired but it's soft so pulled it off.

ascents.name: Rain Dance
ascents.comment: Rad compression line. Few goes. Thanks for the spraydown Josh and congrats on the send!

ascents.name: Diabolique
ascents.comment: Few goes. Knee bars are tricky. Really cool sequence!

ascents.name: Diamondback
ascents.comment: Nice new one from D woods. Awesome feature with cool movement, unfortunately a bit sandy at the bottom. Pretty cold out today... Few suss goes then a few send goes.

ascents.name: Te Cuelgas Guey Stand
ascents.comment: When did the world cup move outdoors. Crazy sequence, unbelievable that it's the best way to do it. Some day Chris will climb V10. Pulled it out of my butt day 2.

ascents.name: Thug Mansion
ascents.comment: Hard til it wasn't. Tristan gave me beta and it worked I'll be darned! Fell a couple times at the lip being sloppy but when it went it went silky smooth.

ascents.name: Child Stars
ascents.comment: Slid off the top in the wet snow at the end of last season twice, thought about taking it but didn't. Came back and it was even easier than I remembered.

ascents.name: The Demon
ascents.comment: Flailed for a while, on the first move, had about 20 goes of getting a tiny bit closer, then finally Tristan sent and I followed him up for the send train. Mike said I could lock it off if I was tall, but then my foot was in my face and he was wrong. Miserable boulder fun session.

ascents.name: Blood Money
ascents.comment: Fun climbing with less dab potensh than you'd think looking at it. Fell off the end on the flash go, sent quickly after. Inspiring watching Dean bag it last minute... Unsure of grade prob slasher.

ascents.name: The Shining
ascents.comment: Pretty good flash go, but couldn't pull it off. Sent a few goes later. Rad roof, cool movement, and seems accessible to all sizes.

ascents.name: Room Service
ascents.comment: My biceps hurt so much from squeezing close compression all trip long. Bailed off the end first session cuz I was scared, glad the last rainy day turned out to be a great climbing day with sticky conditions so I could leave Squam with no regrets! Cool movement on weird holds, with a little spice.

ascents.name: The Chickening
ascents.comment: New age classic, Reckoning into Big Chicken. If it didn't off route the lip and the right arete would actually be really sick. Fun resistance climbing to a redpoint cruxy last pull on Big Chicken... If I stop now today is a rest day. Bryce got the Yatta train!

ascents.name: The Squaminator
ascents.comment: Sort of close on flash. But then took a while to figure out the last move so maybe not... hot and smarmy but Bryce and I still pulled it off!

ascents.name: Shelter
ascents.comment: Pure, aesthetic, and SICK! So psyched to climb this one. Thought about it a lot and just can't take it. Felt easier than just about everything else this trip including Busted V5. Bryce sent one go off of the train.

ascents.name: Leviathan style
ascents.comment: First big move is kinda tough. So many palm flappers... Well Tristan and I did not get 50 points today.

ascents.name: Cat Ranch
ascents.comment: Cool beta intensive resistance problem. Tried during a tired after work sesh with Eric, then came back 15 hours later and dispatched first go. Does that count as one session? Tim says the topout crack is 5.9

ascents.name: Sunseeker
ascents.comment: Striking line with interesting movement, a full value topout, and a spectacular view. Add the sense of urgency provided by a rapidly melting landing and long approach, and you get a line that really feels worth it. Best hard line I have seen in CO. Felt easy for 12.

ascents.name: The Hatchet
ascents.comment: Failed during a tired evening sesh. Came back, watched the boys flail "last go"s on the belly for 2 hours in slippery conditions then fired 2nd go. Also got reported for spray painting the boulder, but the cop knew what was up. Fun one Zach! Let the after work night seshes re-commence!

ascents.name: Log Cabins
ascents.comment: Super cool moves on smooth feet and at times sharp holds. 4 goes, I guess super low end or just 11 but I'm grading soft now so whatever. Proj is... doable?

ascents.name: Formula 500
ascents.comment: Lot easier than Dark Waters, I'm with Purdy. Just gotta keep climbing contrivances and sit starts in this cave until I feel some sense of fulfillment.

ascents.name: Ain't no heaven for a thug
ascents.comment: Need to learn how to turn my toes in. Personally difficult, but obviously not that difficult because I did it pretty quick. Glad I didn't have to campus the crux move.

ascents.name: Formula 50 Super Sit
ascents.comment: Pretty lowball, pretty stupid, and pretty hard. I came in like a wrecking ball...

ascents.name: Muddy Waters
ascents.comment: So hard for me. Today especially... end of DW is piss not sure if it even adds difficulty. But the beginning is so heinous.

ascents.name: Temper Tantrum
ascents.comment: Start doesn't add much but I'll take it. Had some trouble executing but sent in a few goes.

ascents.name: The Heist
ascents.comment: Beautiful impressive wall with good movement. Quite the stunner! Tag teamed with Jeremy.

ascents.name: William Shatner
ascents.comment: That's a damn good boulder. Spent way too much time trying and failing on this when tired, felt pretty easy fresh. Topout was a wee bit scary going straight up...

ascents.name: Both Sides of the Spectrum
ascents.comment: Simple but with such subtleties. Was not expecting to send this so fast, felt impossible... until it went.

ascents.name: Naked and Afraid
ascents.comment: 5ish tries. Cool sequence, went for straightforward beta at the top. "Hard topouts" are proving to be pretty hilarious in CO. Could be 11...

ascents.name: The Exfoliator
ascents.comment: I must have been very fat last time because this time it felt quite reasonable. Just gotta get the bike to slide in right on the first move, no double clutchery required.

ascents.name: Little House on the Prairie
ascents.comment: What a tiny little pile. Kind of fun tho. Felt crazy hard for two sessions then Chris came out to watch and damn it was easy.

ascents.name: Secret Splendour
ascents.comment: Good moves on a small problem. M flash after a rough hot and tired first session. Got fluke cold conditions for two hours and got to this on the tail end of that and it felt crazy easy. Then it got hot again for nbs. Chen and Withey injured... just me and Kim on the send squad, although Chris did gimp flash up autobot and tommys

ascents.name: Death Trout
ascents.comment: Super cool sequence and fun climbing. Blew the fraish, but still got to follow Jeremy up for a send train!

ascents.name: Dismantling the Enemy
ascents.comment: Few goes, used shoulder match beta to make it fit me better. Dabby AF but it's an OK line.

ascents.name: Rain Maker
ascents.comment: Fun squeeze problem with weird moves and a hold I have never experienced before. Punted once but redeemed shortly thereafter. The slab was quite chossy and scary...

ascents.name: Evil Backwards
ascents.comment: I knew I was going to send when I finally stuck the crux move in isolation once and had the climb in 5 non overlapping parts. First fluke in a while!

ascents.name: Bebe Wolverine
ascents.comment: So frustrating, but also pretty cool. 2 flukes in a day! Heel placed terribly, panicked and my foot somehow fell into a bomber toehook position. Much wow.

ascents.name: Carnage
ascents.comment: D O P line with a super satisfying stick at the end. 2 sessions, go in the morning so you don't get sun in your face.

ascents.name: Mental Masturbation
ascents.comment: Surprisingly the ass dragging sit doesn't make the stand any better. But it did make me tired enough to almost slice my entire pinky open on the jug. Good thing I bailed, sent a short while later. Never. Ever. Again.

ascents.name: No More Greener Grasses
ascents.comment: YES! Tried a few years ago and it felt really hard, sent in a couple goes first day of the season this time. What a beautiful line with sick movement!

ascents.name: Double Dutchez
ascents.comment: Miserable and very hard for me. Bryce saved me with hybrid heel beta. 3rd session, some piles are harder to climb than others...

ascents.name: Storm shadow
ascents.comment: Very soft, but I'll take it. Surprisingly easy for me to use the undercling pinch, I must be evolving. Bryce punted the stand a few times but did both, which was sick.

ascents.name: Lost in Space
ascents.comment: You get lucky or you don't on this one. Got a solid spraydown from the crew and got lucky!

ascents.name: The Power of Ten
ascents.comment: Really weird problem. Felt impossible until I got the positioning just right, and moved the left foot wider. Then it went immediately. Thanks Dustin for leading the charge!

ascents.name: Grundle City Direct
ascents.comment: Couldn't do the normal one so this seemed easier. A few goes. Awesome movement.

ascents.name: Mind Matters
ascents.comment: Felt tough to me, used the shorty method to make it high percentage. Looks like we were the first ones there this season...

ascents.name: Burnout
ascents.comment: Not a good style for your boy but pulled it out desperately a long ways into the session. Sick line! I will get in shape yet!

ascents.name: Testify
ascents.comment: This has to be the boulder that least suits my body. Undercling twisted 20 degrees beyond my already damaged wrist's range of motion leads to a full body rip in  a 3 foot tall roof. How did I not dab or break my wrist. Also fell off the end once wow. Only redeeming quality for me was fist bumping the tree I was hanging onto and dropping.

ascents.name: The Shield
ascents.comment: Back to back with Bryce... was incredibly psyched upon flashing this dream line, but so much more psyched when Bryce flash trained it! Unreal, a moment I will never forget. Gorgeous looking line that climbs perfectly. Holy shit excellent.

ascents.name: A Maze of Death
ascents.comment: Glad to see I'm stronger than I was 4 years ago! M flashed. Alex gave a million goes, but will send easily when fresh... Almost had a sick no fall day if I hadn't tried Haroun. Curse you Haroun!!!

ascents.name: Buttermilker
ascents.comment: From the stand. Had it in 2 majorly overlapping parts 4 years ago, but everyone does and can't do it. Until it's soft of course. Psyched to finally put it down...

ascents.name: Dominator
ascents.comment: Best day of climbing for me ever. Almost was already with Abby and Phonebook before this, but now it's just surreal. Reverted to the heel hook method because it felt easy, even though I don't like it. Feels like solid 12 with the heel, at least 13 OG method. Abbatoir is harder for sure. Never thought I would see the day... YATTA!!!

ascents.name: Atlas Shrugged
ascents.comment: Sick compression on improbably bad holds. No move is too hard but linking it all up is exhausting; never been more tired topping out a boulder. Hard for me because I'm lousy on slopers, but pulled it off somehow. Also no good when it's too cold and dry, had to moisten both hand and hold to send in the 3rd session. Psyched!

ascents.name: Power slave
ascents.comment: Super dumpy but cool movement on weird unpleasant holds. Figured out the beta in a few tries with Mike then sent. Will never do Ackrite nor Redirect.

ascents.name: Hungry Hungry Hippos
ascents.comment: Amazing line, Vice of Red Rocks for sure. Except lower angle. Gonna keep drawing comparisons here. Felt solid to me but it was hot today and I don't like close compression underclings. Had no friction at the top, had to resort to bs chalking maneuvers to send... Still managed it in a session though.

ascents.name: Under the Skin
ascents.comment: Surprised myself and Mark with the day 1 fluke after a miserable day at Mortar. Nice moves, although there is somehow still a sharp hold. Def a body position boulder, once you're in the positions it's not so bad. Impossible trav gets the didn't go soft from Mark and I.

ascents.name: Fisting the Sky
ascents.comment: Nice low start to Touching. Had to do it for the name. Day is shaping up to be nice after everything was soaking wet at 3AM last night and it was pouring rain still and Bryce and I were depressed but now it's beautiful and look where we are

ascents.name: High Lonesome Rambler
ascents.comment: Super fun one way at the top of the talus field. Interesting face crimp compression into full blastoff for the lip over a weird landing... sweet. Shoutout to Dor Damien BK and Jess for hiking up and giving support! Super softy at 12 or maybe 11...

ascents.name: The Art of War
ascents.comment: Never thought this would go, but it wasn't so bad, sent 2nd try from the start. Spent almost 3 minutes navigating the 720 degrees of kneebar rotations, but pulled it out in the end. Very entertaining and difficult for me, but soft because the hardest move is probably V7.

ascents.name: The Power of Bar One
ascents.comment: So fucked, def the hardest problem I've done this trip but also a one mover so who knows... if it truly is a V12 one mover that would be the hardest move I have ever done, and that feels about right. I can see how it would be really easy if you're strong, but I'm not. Guess it's soft. Thanks for the beer Will! 75th double d of the trip!!!

ascents.name: Barracuda sds
ascents.comment: Pretty unpleasant, don't get the hype. Guess it is a cool line, with a more obvious start than the stand. These safety ticks are getting heinous.

ascents.name: Monkey business
ascents.comment: Almost flash trained my first 8B+ with Bryce, would have been sick. Did it a few goes later.

ascents.name: Derailed
ascents.comment: Too many rest days so we went out in the rain, and somehow despite the boulder being soaked all the holds were dry. Sent in the dark in just my undies and a kneepad. Psyched on my first 8B+.

ascents.name: Black shadow
ascents.comment: Very nice, too pumped after a long day of climbing first session on it, but that just opened up the M Flash. Ethan's first 8B soon!

ascents.name: Green Mamba
ascents.comment: Felt hard for me but only because I don't like the holds much. Wasn't doing so hot until Bryce send... but obviously send trained on his heels.

ascents.name: Armed response
ascents.comment: Felt like solid V12 to me, had a really hard time getting my ass/earth magnet off the ground. After the first move it isn't too bad though. Great movement, aesthetically not the greatest.

ascents.name: El corazon
ascents.comment: Flash go was kind of a wash, but psyched to do this line fast! Best hard line so far... Nate sent right after.

ascents.name: Steak house
ascents.comment: Super softy could be easier but first 12 fraisher helll yeaaa. Spock pinch is sick!

ascents.name: Oral Office
ascents.comment: This and Pendragon have been the only things that have taken me more than a session so far... Fun dyno! Super annoying start.

ascents.name: Industry of cool
ascents.comment: Yesssss really wanted to do this one bad, definitely a trip goal. First hard one would be a dyno! Brotha B led the way this time and I followed, but had to rapid fire for an hour to make it happen. Felt unreal to stick the slot, so psyched on this probably easier than V12 gimmick! I leave you with wise words from Brotha B, "It's impossible to grade, but it's definitely not 13".

ascents.name: Snappy Sit
ascents.comment: Hell yes! Trip dubbed at Mortar how the hell did this happen. After the stand went sit only took a few tries. Mortar lvl up day.

ascents.name: Phantom Limb
ascents.comment: Another super softy, but similar to rumble with a much harder crux at the end of the problem. My toehooking is definitely leveling up. Thought I wasn't gonna do it til I said last go and it was soft

ascents.name: Bleeding Brothers
ascents.comment: Ringing in the new year with a super improbable send of this thing. So fun and unique with monster toehook compression.

ascents.name: Full Monty
ascents.comment: First one I've fluked in a while. Couldn't do any of the moves, then I could barely do the crux moves, so I just tried it from the start and it somehow didn't feel that difficult.

ascents.name: Hand Of Perseus
ascents.comment: Few tries, sick problem that works well for me. Movement is great, sloper is sick, and dat blue schist doh. Could be 11 but I'll take this one. Repeated it for the insta. Mark and I had a case of the Mondays...

ascents.name: Yabo Roof
ascents.comment: This is my favorite hard line to date. First go of the season. 3 sessions, but all I really needed was toe rubber instead of a velcro strap. Sick moves, perfect rock, tall questy topout... surely this is the stuff of legends.

ascents.name: The Holy Rails SDS
ascents.comment:
Without a doubt one of the proudest and hardest lines I have had the privilege of climbing on. The whole Sandbox came to give pads and support, and I surprised myself (and everyone else) by sending second go from the sit. Perfect conditions and a move that couldn't be more my style landed this in the 12 range for me. So damn psyched to take this down and continue taking on the never ending gauntlet set by Max, Mark, and all the Nor Cal crew. Happy fucking Halloween!

Edit: 200th double digit! Woohoo!

ascents.name: Boyz in the Hood
ascents.comment: This one was really a lot of fun to climb on. Felt impossible til I realized I just needed to skip any hold that wasn't a jug. Feels great to be pushing my limits again. Shout out to Shirley and Obe-I mean Stoffel for bringing pads and camaraderie!

ascents.name: One love
ascents.comment: Lowball day, 10 tries. Less than 2 stars, more than 1, and easier than all the things Max pisses on in the gym. Also did the dumb bulge proj around the corner, it's an awkward 6.

ascents.name: Shadow Warrior
ascents.comment: Punted and would have gone back first onto rock if Brooks hadn't saved me. Sent next go. Finally put a hard one down in the Valley!

ascents.name: Gentlemen's Project Sit
ascents.comment: Finally got my Piplup. And Pupitar evolved, but he's off the team for reasons which will remain undisclosed

ascents.name: The Tea Cup
ascents.comment: Found tall man beta with an intermediate. Today was a good day

ascents.name: The Ram
ascents.comment: Pinch control. Legendary.

ascents.name: Turbulence
ascents.comment: I love turby

ascents.name: Somewhere in Time
ascents.comment: 3 sessions, first hard team yerrow send! Puccio better watch out... Or not... Too strong. Awesome black mountain style boulder, last thing I had to do before leaving So Cal

ascents.name: Lonesome Animals
ascents.comment: Apparently I can only climb 10 or 12 in joes. Awesome line! Crossed the dam in swift water to get to this guy, went down in 15 minutes or so. Probably significantly harder if you are short. Damn boulders are awesome!

ascents.name: Mandala
ascents.comment: After punting off the top for 3 sessions I finally made it. So psyched, one of the last boulders I had to do this season. Felt easy today... So it's soft

ascents.name: Bang On
ascents.comment: Never thought my first 12 would go this quickly! Handful of goes. Psyched to break my mental barrier on such a D O P problem

ascents.name: Jigsaw
ascents.comment: Big moment for me, conquering the nemesis. 7th session nbd pretty sure it's low end for the grade. Tried incredibly hard, and forced it out. My proudest send of the year undoubtedly. Can't wait to see what the future has in store for me now.

ascents.name: Counter Clockwork
ascents.comment: Not ideal conditions in the sun but still went cuz it's soft. Exited naturally, contrived exit looks cool too but not like a different boulder at all. My 200th 8a?

ascents.name: Le Bâtard
ascents.comment: Same difficulty as atresie, so pretty darn soft. I wish it would stop being so humid water is just appearing out of thin air on everything.

ascents.name: Magneton
ascents.comment: Nice one with a cool sloper. Bit contrived tho.

ascents.name: Big golden assis
ascents.comment: When you get one day of climbing after 2 rainy days before 2 rainy days really nothing is off limits.

ascents.name: Atresie
ascents.comment: Easiest of the 5? Also when did they add this I thought I was done.

ascents.name: T-Rex assis
ascents.comment: Few tries. Had to refine the lower sequence to keep chalk on my hands.

ascents.name: Bérézina-Carnage combinaison assis
ascents.comment: Not too hard. Just gotta do abbatoir and apotheose sit now to finish the boulder.

ascents.name: Muttertag
ascents.comment: Brutal. Got revenge on last day cleanup day! Right hand method. Some funny videos out there of people jumping off the ground...

ascents.name: *Free for all
ascents.comment: Few tries. Cleanup day success, managed 3 double digits inside 30 min to wrap up the day.

ascents.name: Jack's broken heart
ascents.comment: Good flash go, prob should have done it. Took a few tries instead. What a cool position!

ascents.name: Giulebbatici geni gerosolimitani
ascents.comment: Start waay down in the hole. Felt hard to me! Also what's up with microcosmos.

ascents.name: Body count
ascents.comment: Hard until I started using the correct beta. Fun, and a bit of an involved downclimb. That left hand niblet is painful!

ascents.name: *Unendliche Geschichte 2
ascents.comment: Some really embarrassing flash goes going down on this slipper chipped river rock. Fun climbing!

ascents.name: *Sofa Surfer
ascents.comment: Few goes, repairing my battered ego after muttertag. Friends arriving soon!

ascents.name: Octopussy
ascents.comment: Super softy, very fun though. First problem of the day!

ascents.name: Foxy Lady
ascents.comment: Little suspect grade wise but fun problem with cool movement.

ascents.name: Intermezzo left
ascents.comment: Fun contrivance, prob would have flashed with better betas...

ascents.name: Nipple Ninja
ascents.comment: Couple tries, prob 10/11. Really fun moves on cool holds!

ascents.name: Like Ghosts
ascents.comment: Took a bit of effort, had to work out the right beta. Plus undercling pinches not my specialty... pinch training day for Tim!

ascents.name: Chad’s Roof
ascents.comment: Kind of hard not to dab. Realized it wasn't that bad with a heel instead of a toe, then bagged it. Tristan could have flashed... but did it "solidly" after a little sussing on his next go from the start.

ascents.name: Toxic Shock Lower than the Low Start Start SDS
ascents.comment: Possible FA of incredible choss, certainly did not think I would be doing a problem I hadn't done before today, but imagine the joy and surprise in my eyes to spot a lower undercling below the existing low start of Toxic Shock. Griffin probably already did this, but if not what an incredible and historic first and then second ascent I have claimed.

ascents.name: Free Basin
ascents.comment: 4 Sessions, 8+ hours. Worth every penny. Held the ultimately extended king swing and just barely grazed a pad. I'm really leveling up these days.

ascents.name: Mysterious Wayz
ascents.comment: Nootz

ascents.name: Mobbin' Around
ascents.comment: Went straight to the flat gaston then locked off to the last hold. Again, why do I ever try to use all the holds. Washed day in CC

ascents.name: Left graham arete
ascents.comment: Took a while to figure out, but between sussing and trying really hard eventually got it to go in a fairly controlled way. Mega classic

ascents.name: The Art of Flight
ascents.comment: It goes boys. Second double d in CO this year. Productivity is at an all time high!

ascents.name: Mavericks
ascents.comment: Fun pure line! Prob shoulda flashed... got a couple more boulders on Tristan now ;)

ascents.name: The Goblin
ascents.comment: Few goes. Was definitely raining, but the holds weren't too moist until the ledge at the top. That was soaked so I dropped off but I need the points so I'm taking it.

ascents.name: Off the Books
ascents.comment: Lotta different ways to do this one, had to hybridize when the toe wasn't staying. Everything in this roof is really cool and immensely shitty at the same time.

ascents.name: The rhino
ascents.comment: Wrecked on the last day but barely pullet it off. If I have a talent it is climbing V11 and under.

ascents.name: Schwerer Gustov
ascents.comment: So ludicrously hard for me. No knee bars, no feet first, all suffering and struggling. When I say it's soft V11 I mean it's actually hard but I feel bad with how many people have downgraded it regardless of how they did it.

ascents.name: Anal Intruder #10
ascents.comment: Kinda hard, but not even close to as bad as I remembered. Tristan and I did anal, then we did a climb too.

ascents.name: A New Map Of Hell
ascents.comment: End of the day desperation send. Two fingers on the good crimp, triple pull up to the the back two on the numb desperate top out. I won’t do slashface this trip but at least I did the better line he said

ascents.name: El chupacabra right
ascents.comment: Send train with Tristan. Could just keep the kneebar. I think my guide is somewhere around here.

ascents.name: Canopener
ascents.comment: Had to try really hard. Kind of cool, too many hold options its overwhelming. Barely stuck the jump, desperate. Missed the send train with Bryce by 1...

ascents.name: Ground Control
ascents.comment: In a few goes. Got the cam to stay and didn't have to rip! Very odd problem, fun but low.

ascents.name: Blackie
ascents.comment: Hard for me. Struggled it out, the one time pinching matters outside.

ascents.name: Golden rows of flows
ascents.comment: Weirder than it is hard. Used the fabled down bump on this one to make the box fit me. Paul Justin and Emily were just making it look so fun we had to try.

ascents.name: The Drowning Grip
ascents.comment: After a heinous first session with a scary wet fire off the pinch somehow pulled it off. Glad I could just reach through the top instead of using the wormy undercling... Psyched to do this one! Finally getting my vert and slab feet back just in time to go back to CO and forget it all again. Surprised and happy to pull it off. Not sure what the weakest climber who could do this is but I'm pretty sure they climb less than V11... well whatever. Trip dub on the last day!

ascents.name: Now Nudda
ascents.comment: Super fun, pretty hard. Didn't jump but the cut was gnar. In the dark in the rain with Tim and Josh

ascents.name: Eternia
ascents.comment: A few goes shame on me. Fun climbing on jugs to a cool feet first exit.

ascents.name: Left el Jorge
ascents.comment: Hard for me for some reason. Had to use the sidepull to get leverage cuz my legs are weak. Fuck you Tim day was going great until Chris' knee exploded.

ascents.name: Immortality Sit Start
ascents.comment: Was told this was V10 but felt harder. Couple unpleasant moves into the stand.

ascents.name: Echale (stand)
ascents.comment: Slow progress on this one. Gonna be a long time

ascents.name: Veritas Assis
ascents.comment: Hard for me for some reason. Not hard enough though pulled it off desperate boy style.

ascents.name: Super Botslayer
ascents.comment: Everything here sucks but at least it's easy.

ascents.name: Authentic Battle Damage
ascents.comment: Crux is excavating your way to the start holds and then figuring out which of them to use. Probably started close to the right place, left hand crimp right hand on the arete same height as the crimp. Not terribly hard once you pull on, and not terribly enjoyable either.

ascents.name: Belly of the Beast
ascents.comment: Tough for me. Polished stone on a cold day is pretty slippery... weird mantle onto the slab. Had a good flash go then regressed for a few goes until I finally squeezed up the dang thing.

ascents.name: Carpet Bombers Variation
ascents.comment: Project eliminating the large sloper from Carpet Bombers. End of trip fitness burn, almost pumped off of the top so tired...

ascents.name: Ricky Moss
ascents.comment: Guess it's a bit harder than no tiempo, so if that's 10 than 11 seems right. Pretty fun.

ascents.name: Anybody?
ascents.comment: Possible FA to the right of Nobody. Squat start on low left sidepull higher right sidepull. Desperate cross saht to the lip, and some trickery leads to a desperate mantle onto the sandy beach slab.

ascents.name: Prospectors
ascents.comment: Barely could do the first move, but I could and its underclings so prob soft for the grade. Sent first time I pulled off the ground enough to move.

ascents.name: Anger Management
ascents.comment: Cool moves around a sort of heinous crux hold. Luckily, you use it for 2 moves then recycle it for a few more so thats good.

ascents.name: Mcmurphey
ascents.comment: Few tries. Don't think any V10 climbers will be doing this any time soon. The direct dyno is sick! Good find Alex.

ascents.name: Tetris
ascents.comment: Cool movement, a little dabby as always. Solid after work sesh with Eric and Tim, got it in a few tries.

ascents.name: Love Mattress
ascents.comment: Pretty hard. But went first go with the right beta so must be soft.

ascents.name: Kneez in the Trap
ascents.comment: Purdy beta on this one. Super fun, and great rock!

ascents.name: NBA Pro Jams
ascents.comment: Took a long session to figure it out, but it was like 70 degrees out. Dey axed me if I wants to come back when it's colder, and I says no. Man's not hot.

ascents.name: Dragon's Claw
ascents.comment: Was told it was Topaz and I was like that shit's easy. Realized it wasn't and then it was kinda hard. Was starting lying down on the rail, that was lame, finally got it to come together from the crimp start just to realize my beta was so wack. Went to the crimp, crossed again to the shit block slot, then tensioned into the jug. Felt like 12 but that was bad beta so soft 11.

ascents.name: Mesmerizer
ascents.comment: I hate this side of the boulder but I'll never be done with it. Nice having the bro out for a weekend!

ascents.name: Attack on Titan
ascents.comment: Nice one Nick! Shoulder was not pleased with the abuse on the high percentage beta but it can deal with it.

ascents.name: Diagonal
ascents.comment: Actually pretty fun, double clutched at the lip. Kinda hard...

ascents.name: The Great War for Civilisation
ascents.comment: This isn't what I wanted. But it's what I get. Taking the soft high grade on this one. You either die a hero or live long enough to see yourself become the villain.

ascents.name: Marble Sit
ascents.comment: Got tired, pulled it off at limit. Easy climbs made hard woohoo. Jeremy owes me Baba's

ascents.name: Wildcat
ascents.comment: Had to use a knee pad too tired omg. Lots of beta and stuff.

ascents.name: The Overcling Traverse
ascents.comment: Eric thought I might flash it and it happened. Fancy that! Super fun. Low end at my height.

ascents.name: Running Scared
ascents.comment: Glad I hiked up here just for this. 7 grades harder than Gobot.

ascents.name: The Kind Traverse
ascents.comment: Cool for a trav. Moves well, kinda dabby tho. Any of those moves would be really sick on a face climb but when you do 7 of them in a row and are still touching the ground they somehow lose their novelty.

ascents.name: Powaqqatsi
ascents.comment: 10/11 not really sure. Taking the grade because the start jug was soaking and water dripped in my face mid ascent. First go after doing the stand, felt easier musta climbed it better.

ascents.name: Lost
ascents.comment: Very straightforward and soft.

ascents.name: Barrel Rider Stand
ascents.comment: From the jug. Nice climb in and of itself, legit start has some sick moves and is a lot of climbing!

ascents.name: The Nickness Right
ascents.comment: Sussed it out with tired fingers and body, and then forced it hard. Need a rest day! Like this area.

ascents.name: Elegant Universe
ascents.comment: A few tries. First move is really hard for me. Got so damn lost getting here, had to do it fast before the sun set. Def harder than lost, have to retro UG

ascents.name: Dark Horse Sit
ascents.comment: Few goes. These long boulders are really tiring... gonna be in good shape soon!

ascents.name: Stanley Kubrick sds
ascents.comment: 2nd go from the sit start. That lowball down the hill is pretty hard.

ascents.name: Bambi
ascents.comment: 1st go. Always thought that this would be my first V12, so it makes sense that it's actually easier. Shoulda tried to flash, messed around on the moves before trying to warm up.

ascents.name: Fantasia Stand
ascents.comment: Sick problem with an improbable sequence. Harder than Bambi for me.

ascents.name: Big Joe Left
ascents.comment: 5 sessions or more? W/e befuddled by this one forever, Drewbie's reachy beta made it possible. Still hard for me though. Dropping off of a contrived problem in the rain never felt so good, so desperate for rock climbing

ascents.name: Big Gulp
ascents.comment: Hard for me. End move wasn't easy but stuck the first move finally once and forced it hard.

ascents.name: Underworld Ext.
ascents.comment: Little extra spice with the bigger dyno. Huge dyno variation would be really hard from the start.

ascents.name: God Module
ascents.comment: Yatta! Bryce clinched the flash train for his first 8A flash, super proud! Felt terrible this morning but tried hard and climbed surprisingly well. Pure.

ascents.name: Sharpen your teeth
ascents.comment: 3 or 4 goes. 1st move is really easy but the rest of it is kinda hard if you're weak like me.

ascents.name: Vapor Lock
ascents.comment: Lots of sussing, 1st go from the start. Mark flash? ;) had one shot, barely pulled it off. Way too much climbing.

ascents.name: The Law
ascents.comment: Tried hard, almost fell off a couple times. Definitely got lucky on this one. Psyched!

ascents.name: Bound by Tension
ascents.comment: Low sand makes this kind of sick. Dunno why this took me so long, Could be 10 but I'm taking high grades now so I can call them soft. Chillin with Dylan on X mas eve

ascents.name: All You Need is Nub
ascents.comment: Or is it? 3 star rock quality and movement with 0 star height. Shout out to Max for cleaning and spotting this one. On the boulder sitting atop Skunk Sandwich and Leprechaun.

ascents.name: Lethal design
ascents.comment: Was hoping I would M flash this after my miserable sessions a couple years ago, and this time with bullet skin pulled it off with no warmup. Hardest move is maybe V7. Used Pete Lowe OG beta. Happy to be done with this...

ascents.name: Abaddon
ascents.comment: Took the swing once and landed perfectly just at the edge of the pit with no pads in sight. After almost dying decided to change my beta to keep the foot on. Such a cool problem!

ascents.name: Thuggish Ruggish
ascents.comment: Cool campus problem by Austin Geiman on a sweet pinch... has MZ written all over it. Slightly harder than the other campus I thought was 10 so I guess 11. 2nd?

ascents.name: We Need Ice
ascents.comment: Felt tough but I know it's soft. Pretty cool moves, at times awkward. Nice flash Chen!

ascents.name: Ringtail
ascents.comment: Super fun weird vertical toe hook-crappy sloper compression. Very physical and bizarre.

ascents.name: Touching the sky
ascents.comment: Easy if you're tall and can lock off. Amazing boulder with amazing movement. So good!

ascents.name: White Dwarf
ascents.comment: So named after much deliberation for it's short stature and condensed difficulty, as well as to jab at the kid who punted the FA 4 times on the last move. In classic fluke fashion... SNAKE! Thanks for the tour Jake! Low start on 2 underclings to the double undercling up road from the main parking lot. 2 methods, Bryce's felt impossible. Started getting desperate on this one and almost lost the big day...

ascents.name: Cubic Zirconia
ascents.comment: Felt about as difficult as Roses, but some last minute beta tweaks made it feel easier... hmm. Very nice problem! Still fighting hard for every send I can get my arse up.

ascents.name: Busted Shadow
ascents.comment: Glad I could be here for Bryce's Northeast trip! He is really killing it.

ascents.name: Quasimoto
ascents.comment: Can a triple double be any more desperate than this? Was within a couple goes of giving up on every single climb I did today. Fighting hard.

ascents.name: Trinity
ascents.comment: I would call this soft but it took me 2 hours and I almost didn't do it. Ran out of excuses on this one, I think I'm just really weak. Barely pulled it out, fingers are screaming.

ascents.name: Out Of Your League
ascents.comment: Almost M-flashed from the low today. Must have been really weak last year this felt impossible. Nice to be back, I love it here!

ascents.name: Thunderbird
ascents.comment: A bit late to the party with this one, but really psyched to climb it after repeatedly greasing off the top last time. Great line, great weekend with lil D in the meadows.

ascents.name: Thunderhead
ascents.comment: Easier than T-bird for sure, so soft 11 seems fair. Back to back sends of T-bird then this one, psyched!

ascents.name: Ribbefett
ascents.comment: This is the kind of sequence and movement setters have wet dreams about creating. Intricate foot and hand sequence up a sick fin. Tried it on the way in, couldn't pull on due to glassy skin and warm weather, then came back after a full day and sieged for a few hours, steadily losing stamina but cleaning up my sequence just enough to validate continuing the session. Full value for me in these conditions, but if it's cold and I'm not weak could be super soft...

ascents.name: Zodiac
ascents.comment: Found a crimp out right makes this a lot easier! But seriously, kind of cool for a contrivance.

ascents.name: One and Done
ascents.comment: For those of us who are way too weak to do both dynos on Encore, I pioneered a lame and weak way to top out after the first dyno. Yayyyy me!

ascents.name: Marlboro man
ascents.comment: 3rd ish go, great rock, super softy! Not a fan of the underclings though...

ascents.name: In Search Of The New Sound
ascents.comment: Besides the obvious jug rail following the climb the whole time, the kind of heinous holds, and the lowball nature of it, it's actually ok.

ascents.name: Captain Graffiti
ascents.comment: Call me Captain Choss because I spent the last 3 hours screaming, cussing, and battling my way through four mediocre to chossy boulders (plus a fail on Skobbejak). Yatta!

ascents.name: The Midnight Barber
ascents.comment: Best one of the day, wish I had some more pads to try the cool stuff. Moves well, not a good warmup though.

ascents.name: Purple Nipple Clan
ascents.comment: Really hard for me but so many dgs it must be soft...

ascents.name: Shallow Cave
ascents.comment: Lowball underclings? Sick. Psyched it was raining otherwise I wouldn't have slid off the V0 topout once before sending. Probably my favorite lowball undercling V11 cave in 8 day rain.

ascents.name: Gogoan Stand
ascents.comment: Definitely said I would never try this, but Yatta Boys were having such an epic day we had to get on it. Both sent easily, difficulty of the full line is dubious...

ascents.name: Brown Shadow
ascents.comment: Hate underclings. Still not V12. Yatta boyz sending back to back all day erry day

ascents.name: The hatchling
ascents.comment: Used OG beta felt 11 ish. Also my skin is wet so maybe it's easier... starting to get shut down out here, ready to work for it!

ascents.name: In the Middle of the Ass
ascents.comment: One of the worst climbs I have ever done, but as Brotha B would say, had to hit this one for the "Comedic Value". Mildly raged for a bit, as it felt impossible, but soon found a toe scum to make it easier. Impossible to soft volume 2.

ascents.name: Tea With Elmarie
ascents.comment: Didn't feel too bad, did most of it static except the foot cut sequence. Really cool but a bit contrived, as many lines are out here with all this heavily featured rock.

ascents.name: No Late Benders
ascents.comment: Feeling sick, walking up the hill to the crag was really hard. This felt difficult as well... Safari will be a good chance to recover.

ascents.name: Cthulhu
ascents.comment: So soft I couldn't flash. Weird knee tweaky heel toe cam, but a spectacular problem nonetheless! Views up here are gorgeous too...

ascents.name: Wittness the Sickness
ascents.comment: Hardest climb of the trip for me, but I suck at open hand climbing so def soft 11.  So cool!

ascents.name: The Art Project
ascents.comment: Felt pretty easy and it's not really my style. Honestly no idea on the grade. Super fun movement! Love the heel release jump off the perfect pinch.

ascents.name: Shosholoza
ascents.comment: Felt easier but I'll take 11. So psyched on this line, perfect movement up on it's own pedestal... Trip goal complete.

ascents.name: The Amphitheatre
ascents.comment: Should have known double heels would be the way for me, blew the fraish. Oh well, super sick boulder with amazing pinches!

ascents.name: Pendragon
ascents.comment: Felt hard last session, must have been tired. 1st go today, felt really soft.

ascents.name: Barracuda
ascents.comment: Probably V10. Keep rocklands soft! Super fun! Triple double flash day softies literally at every single turn!

ascents.name: Golden virginia
ascents.comment: 5 goes, hardest 8a in Rocklands yet? Still soft. Way to be Julian!

ascents.name: Royksopp
ascents.comment: Brutal. Hardest flash to date, almost fell at least 3 times but somehow pulled it out. Another one with a sick sequence!

ascents.name: Out of Balance
ascents.comment: Beautiful rock, amazing sequence. Totally numb, cold in the shade today!

ascents.name: Nutsa
ascents.comment: Warmup after Creaking Heights. Knew I wasn't gonna make it a day without trying hard. Felt quite easy, perhaps 10... but when in Rocklands, take the points?

ascents.name: Manitou
ascents.comment: This really made my shoulder sore. Cool movement, definitely contrived. And soft. Are you experienced has gone in 2 parts, no way will I ever link it up though...

ascents.name: Ground Control
ascents.comment: 3rd go. Approached up the wrong gully (classic map-less vague directions) and spent 3 hours finding this. Crux is always finding the boulder in Tahoe. At least it was really really soft! And cool. Would take 10 but all that hiking through manzanitas in shorts was miserable.

ascents.name: Pro Series
ascents.comment: Chris and Bryce were here and they did climb today. Bryce almost flashed, and then didn't do it... Nooooo

ascents.name: Amateur Series
ascents.comment: Glad I never have to do that first awful undercling move again. top of this problem has cool movement, albeit contrived movement...

ascents.name: Hazy Vision
ascents.comment: Harder than gentleman's, and quite similar, so soft 11 seems appropriate. Committed way too hard for a hold I wasn't sure was a jug and took a huge swing that would have landed me 5 feet off the pads if I hadn't held on. Definitely dabbed on Bryce a bit, but at that point it was do or die and I did so I'm counting it.

ascents.name: Ghost of War
ascents.comment: Felt impossible for a long time, which makes sense because Chris crushed it. Finally realized it was soft when I death crimped through the pain.

ascents.name: Man from the past
ascents.comment: I hate underclings. All I have left in Joe's is underclings. 4 or 5 sessions super soft.

ascents.name: Bully
ascents.comment: 4th go. Kind of almost fraished. Worst fraish day ever. Really cool reachy climb, hope everything stays reachy...

ascents.name: The Winged Tiger
ascents.comment: Punted first session but managed to be part of the 2 3 4 train this time. Rad line, feels 11 ish if you avoid taking wing. Dor crushed all her projects today and the sandbox was sending hard too! Great day out in the valley.

ascents.name: Don't Worry Be Snappy
ascents.comment: Been trying this forever, finally felt soft. My mortar breakthrough is at hand! 1st go today right after Go Go Gadget. Nemeses were dropping like it was hot today. Only took me 10 sessions so I'll dg.

ascents.name: Go Go Gadget
ascents.comment: So damn hard for me, sent first try of the sesh today! Keep laughing Will, keep laughing. 5 or 6 sessions, must be soft. Who's gonna do the sit?

ascents.name: Good Vibrations Low
ascents.comment: Came back and did the very bottom move off the low low holds, might bump it to softy 11.

ascents.name: Liane
ascents.comment: Shoulda coulda woulda but didn't frash. 2nd go soft is good too!

ascents.name: Le Chninkel
ascents.comment: Felt really hard but I basically campused the crux section so there is probably better softy beta. Almost fell off the topout. Really glad Dor got me this knee pad its getting some serious mileage out here!

ascents.name: Loaded Direct
ascents.comment: Took a few goes to stick the jump move, but the top is really easy with the knee bar. Feels solid in the grade, probably the standard for 11 in hueco. Soft.

ascents.name: Scream
ascents.comment: Campused out of the pockets, felt heinous. Ice cream looks really hard. Rain and rest days on the horizon.

ascents.name: Rumble in the Jungle
ascents.comment: Super endurancy, fun weird climbing. With so many good holds and so many possible sequences height really doesn't matter

ascents.name: Power of Landjager
ascents.comment: Super softy, another flash courtesy of c Barthel beta. Very good looking line with great moves. Left hand crux hold is kinda uncomfortable tho

ascents.name: El Techo de Los Tres B
ascents.comment: Loses a star for being a lowball but gets it back for having a feet-first section that is heinously fun. Few goes, super fun choss out here!

ascents.name: Barefoot on Sacred Ground
ascents.comment: 1st one in hueco! Sweet choss around here, super fun climbing. Max had the key beta; "well, it makes sense". Want to say I topped out cuz I ain't a weenie, but in reality I just did it cuz it's easy.

ascents.name: Dark Age
ascents.comment: Cool toehooking, easier than barefoot fosho.

ascents.name: Dogwood
ascents.comment: Woohoo! What's not to like about dynoing high off the deck? Psyched to get this thing done.

ascents.name: Global Warming
ascents.comment: Today was a great day for sending problems 2nd go! Brad had the key beta, and ended up getting himself the send as well. Sandbox was unstoppable this weekend.

ascents.name: Dark Matter
ascents.comment: What a line! Felt like the hardest thing I have tried in a long time, until I got back on Boyz. Too much time in Tahoe is making me lose perspective. Solid day by the crew all around, Ty with the flash, Mark with the repeats, Shirley Stoffel and Dor with PflancakeV8, and Will with the 15% lumberjack send!

ascents.name: Hellamental
ascents.comment: Tahoe 8 Star problem!!! 2 lowball moves that actually manage to be kind of fun. Took an ass destroying flop onto bare rock, then got revenge. Watching Ty send with 8B beta was heinous.

ascents.name: Party Animal
ascents.comment: Fell off hand in jug on the flash. Almost flashed my first 8B!!! Would have been so many 8a points, I'm actually really butthurt. Fun climb tho!

ascents.name: The Dead Raccoon
ascents.comment: Was waiting all trip to try this one, psyched to get it done fast. Had to try hard, which was a novelty for this trip.

ascents.name: Gobot
ascents.comment: I can see how someone confused this with Autobot 6B+.

ascents.name: Bush Pilot
ascents.comment: No fall day ended here. Super weird.

ascents.name: Clear Blue Skies
ascents.comment: Dry fired on the flash go, took me 4 tries instead. I'm fat and this still felt easy.

ascents.name: Super Gui
ascents.comment: Few goes. Did it with the mega lock off method, awesome problem!

ascents.name: Kraken
ascents.comment: The only thing that kept me trying this problem for 8+ sessions over 6+ years, through a debilitating wrist injury, was the knowledge that, at some point in the not so distant future, this boulder would be soft. Holy shit excellent.

ascents.name: The Holy Rails
ascents.comment: A few goes. What an amazing line! 4 pads with two 100 pound girls spotting was enough to get the adrenaline pumping. Low end for me, but also my favorite kind of move. Psyched on this thing!

ascents.name: 🔥 in the Hole
ascents.comment: A nice addition to the boulder by Max and crew. Fun and pumpy

ascents.name: Polar Opposites
ascents.comment: Nothing like some fatboi climbing!

ascents.name: The Geode
ascents.comment: This looked bigger in the picture

ascents.name: Welcome to the Future
ascents.comment: Fun line. Insert classic comment about how I should have done it first go but didn't here.

ascents.name: Claim Jumper
ascents.comment: With 3 consecutive kneebars I found a new appreciation for the time I spent with Bryce during his year of the kneebar.

ascents.name: Stake Your Claim
ascents.comment: Power endurance is the name of the game. Right after Claim Jumper.

ascents.name: The Noble Eightfold Path
ascents.comment: The first of 4 shitty 1 star V11 to V12 mega traverses on the boulder. Comparisons will one day be drawn between these proud lines and other timeless classics such as Bubba Lobotomy. This one starts way low beneath the arete on the double undercling then finishes out Buddha Daze. This could also have a shitty name like Buddha Daze low low as that might be appropriate for a climb this shitty. Someone has probably already done this but was too embarrassed to admit it but I love choss.

ascents.name: Skull
ascents.comment: Double undercling crux. Must be soft.

ascents.name: Kill List
ascents.comment: Jumping and screaming up top after the crux. Good times!

ascents.name: Yabo Face
ascents.comment: Felt easy when it went. 8a is this magical unicorn of a grade. I can't attain it or when I do, it's actually just a donkey wearing a party hat.

ascents.name: March of the pigs
ascents.comment: Thought I was done after a couple hours but then I Fannied it. Bryce is evolving...

ascents.name: Man-Boy
ascents.comment: Used weird beta crossed in left hand to the crimp from the intermediate right hand under the pocket. Climbed well this way, but still reachy...

ascents.name: Prince Of Thieves
ascents.comment: Sketched a bit up top. Revenge after losing a lot of skin

ascents.name: Radiant
ascents.comment: Today is a BIG DAY

ascents.name: Trent's Mom
ascents.comment: The hardest problem I have done in Joe's, and maybe the best. Had to battle for it. At long last, the fabled upgrade...

ascents.name: Monarch
ascents.comment: 3 sessions. Thought the heel was good, tried the toe again and it felt easy

ascents.name: Ebriosity
ascents.comment: Lots of fun to climb. Almost pumped out at the top... Bagged the boulder in a day!

ascents.name: Encore une fois
ascents.comment: None of the moves are hard but both the heel has to be absolutely perfect to send. Heinously low percentage for me, glad it went! Wrapping up some of my old projects here at long last.

ascents.name: Wander Lust
ascents.comment: Felt easier than Body Movement for me... very height dependent. Somewhere between 9 and 12 depending on your height and conditions. Pretty difficult to suss the sequence.

ascents.name: Tour de France Center
ascents.comment: Longest standing project at black, finally goes! just needed the tall guy ghost kneebar beta. super hard, but I realized that all of my climbs say hard and it makes me look weak so it's soft

ascents.name: Chumscrubber
ascents.comment: just had to figure out how to get the heel in, rest was easy. could be v10, could also just be my style

ascents.name: Pussy on the Rag
ascents.comment: Felt really hard, surprised myself by doing it quickly. Sweet bike foot pinch thing to keep body tension. Good moves on a pretty crappy problem

ascents.name: Attack of the Staph Sit
ascents.comment: Awesome line, huge holds perfectly my style. Long, and two bicycles? Pretty DOP

ascents.name: Barely Legal
ascents.comment: Increasing the overlap between me and Chen in joes. Random send, didnt have 2 of the moves, tried it from the start anyways. 3 points!

ascents.name: Beyond Life sit
ascents.comment: 1st go. Hrmmm.... Ill take it! Beyond life is amazing. Shout out... Jess. Retro dg can't live with myself anymore.

ascents.name: Hydrogenated Oil
ascents.comment: Thought it was gonna be v10, but reeling in that mono pocket was hard for me

ascents.name: Gentleman's Project
ascents.comment: Pretty easy... if you're tall. suck it chen

ascents.name: Thunderbird
ascents.comment: hate this shart pile. yaaaa ima do direction for sure easy next time ha chaaaaaa

ascents.name: The Mystery
ascents.comment: really hard for me. super hard. hard moves, but very good. might be v12. soft.

ascents.name: *Raison d'Etre
ascents.comment: very cool. love these boulders. classic me not using the same beta as chen

ascents.name: Book of Nightmares
ascents.comment: Yup this is hard. Nearly scraped my nipple off with the tall-man beta. Worth it.

ascents.name: Ex-patriot
ascents.comment: First time I came to black I knew I had to do this. Good temps and camaraderie helped lots

ascents.name: Shizaam Sit
ascents.comment: Improbable, but it happened somehow. That dyno is wild and generally very strenuous for me. Surprise!

ascents.name: Whiplash
ascents.comment: Big reach and heinous swing. Good stuff

ascents.name: Black hole
ascents.comment: Surprise send. Had it in 3 sketchy parts but it all came together somehow first send go of the day.

ascents.name: The Egg
ascents.comment: 3 years later... Took 3 days to stick the first move once, took it to the top first try! Psyched on this lowball.

ascents.name: Dark Horse
ascents.comment: pity points for the sprained ankle sustained earlier in the day. easier than putting my shoe on was!

ascents.name: Satan's Choice
ascents.comment: blew dat flash. oh well. this is exactly my style!

ascents.name: Crouching Dragon
ascents.comment: just a few tries after flashing the stand. shoulda done it first go!

ascents.name: He Got Game Right
ascents.comment: some crazy moves! good stuff.

ascents.name: Fighting with Alligators
ascents.comment: The 2 year proj goes! Could be easier with absurd endurance... but I don't have that. Just glad I don't have to fall off the last lip traverse ever again.

ascents.name: Agoraphobia
ascents.comment: A few tries. Pretty sweet, stoked I got it!

ascents.name: The Perfect Cave
ascents.comment: just a handful of tries. my first real v11! yayyy

ascents.name: Contrôle Technique
ascents.comment: YES don't know why but this is the one that spoke to me when I got to Font. And of course it ended up being mega for me, 4 sessions fell off of nearly every move multiple times, but finally the 5th session first go it felt so easy. Just had to dial everything in and execute, on these holds the clock is really ticking. The one I would have been really bummed to leave without.

ascents.name: Cent pofs et sans reproche direct
ascents.comment: So humid and moist today hardest thing I could claw up. Topout is scary this contrived way.

ascents.name: Sur-prises assis
ascents.comment: Not too hard but adds enough when the stand is so dicey.

ascents.name: T-Rex
ascents.comment: Closest I've come to flashing a double d here must be a mega softy.

ascents.name: Respire
ascents.comment: Fun movement, forced it the way I knew I could but probably should have done it a better way.

ascents.name: Haute Tension
ascents.comment: Went full epic on this one, almost died dry firing off the lip.

ascents.name: L'Insoutenable Légèreté de L'Etre Debout
ascents.comment: One of the harder mantles I've done...

ascents.name: Hale-Bopp
ascents.comment: Took a while. Gonna have to be tall or have massive hops for this.

ascents.name: Apotheose
ascents.comment: Weird tweaky heel hook. Avoided all the big holds out right

ascents.name: *La Balance
ascents.comment: 2 Sessions. Perfect boulder my favorite kind of climbing (not to  be confused with what I'm good at). Avoided the chipped hold of course.

ascents.name: La Berezina assis
ascents.comment: Not too hard, that crux move on berezina is still weird tho

ascents.name: Berezina-Carnage
ascents.comment: Questionable but everything else here is hard so w/e

ascents.name: Big Golden
ascents.comment: Finished em up. Well I guess there's 5 now so I gotta come back for that other one. Took forever to figure out beta gotta start researching. Ended up with a wild sequence with overhead heel toe cam.

ascents.name: Down under
ascents.comment: WTF hard. At least it's really good. Cleanup day continues!

ascents.name: Rythmo
ascents.comment: Not too hard. Pretty cool movement, almost dropped the flash with a heel slip...

ascents.name: The bomb is explosion
ascents.comment: Sat on one pad, crux was getting off the ground. Not very good but pretty hard so that has to count for something. Nice flash Conor!

ascents.name: Du côté de Seshuan
ascents.comment: That was way more desperate than it should have been. Really flailed up this one, even with sprays from Ishan and Conor.

ascents.name: Conan
ascents.comment: Quite good! Though a bit lowball. Very cool movement and holds, and dare I say it, not one is chipped?

ascents.name: La Dance Sit
ascents.comment: Absolutely brutal. Dragged Caitlin and Conor over here and got savaged by this thing for a while. Tough mantle on slippery stone with a hard pull off the rock as the kicker. Supremely entertaining.

ascents.name: Minisex sit
ascents.comment: Really fun problem with a cool kneebar intro.

ascents.name: Swizz Beats
ascents.comment: From the full sit, felt quite hard. Few hard moves into an interesting mantle.

ascents.name: Piranja
ascents.comment: Tough for me on manufactured holds, they're so slippery. Crux move was easy in iso, but those chipped holds stole my chalk on every send go...

ascents.name: Supersupernova
ascents.comment: This was as far as I was willing to walk for an hour long night sesh.

ascents.name: Puma Pants
ascents.comment: Quite a good one from Griff and Chen right behind now Nudda. Could be easier, but harder from the start than you'd think... I think I doubled my productivity for the summer today with the triple/quad.

ascents.name: The Inspirationist
ascents.comment: Pretty darn cool, psyched to climb new stuff at lincoln. Top is a bit chossy, got up there on the flash and decided to preserve my life by dropping and sussing.

ascents.name: Rail shot
ascents.comment: Fun movement on this one, line right of Behind the 8 Ball. I guess I shouldn't expect that anything at lincoln hasn't been done before at this point...

ascents.name: Deep puddle Dynamics
ascents.comment: Sure felt hard to me. Started from the lowest underclings, top felt very tensiony, super bump in the middle is cool. Rad problem.

ascents.name: Gorillas in the Mist
ascents.comment: Sweet line, rare to see a feature like this. Close compression was too tight, had to match the sloper to go the lip. Tristan with the mega punt, maybe he will send in session number 3.

ascents.name: Cool Arete sit
ascents.comment: Didn't know there was a jug that made this easier, kind of a bummer. Whatever I did felt 10 ish.

ascents.name: Orbital resonance
ascents.comment: First go, but flashed Gandalf first. Cool and scary, though the traverse climbing isn't all that great.

ascents.name: Dump Truck
ascents.comment: Nothing but classics

ascents.name: Shapes and Sizes
ascents.comment: Thought I almost flashed, then realized I couldn't do the move, then went jug to jug skipping all the hard parts and it was really easy. Like really really easy. Trip dub day with Conor on classics only!

ascents.name: Helping Hand
ascents.comment: Warmed up on this one, if someone told me V7 I wouldn't bat an eye. Pretty fun regardless.

ascents.name: The Eighth
ascents.comment: 3rd go shame on me. Guess it was 75 degrees. Sather with the Germ Free takedown!

ascents.name: The Amendment
ascents.comment: Sloppy warm up flash.

ascents.name: Firefly
ascents.comment: Seems like 1 move 10 to me. Not very good or very impressive but hey the rock is good and I hadn't done it. Gotta secure that weekend victory over Tristan.

ascents.name: The Hourglass
ascents.comment: Super cool climb with delicate movements. Slightly marred by the side wall that is right there... rad to see Nina put down the directo!

ascents.name: One Eyed Clown
ascents.comment: Thought I might not do it til I discovered the heel for the crux move. Very cool, certainly not my style. Had to earn it.

ascents.name: *Black Mamba
ascents.comment: Wrong foot beta with good intentions from Austin but I’ll take second go soft soft soooooft

ascents.name: Rogered In The Shower
ascents.comment: The only remarkable things about this boulder are how easy and bad it is

ascents.name: Natural Disaster
ascents.comment: So good. Not a lot of rock this solid around Hueco. 3rd go, what a line! Send train city with T Chen

ascents.name: Wormwood
ascents.comment: Incredible line, pretty intimidating with 3 pads. Tristan and I pulled off the buzzer beater send train with Marcus telling us we had to leave as I was sending. Last problem of the year, and top contender for best. Haven't been scared like that in a little bit! Tristan got drunk too and said a lot of nice things to me including that he was glad I was there ;)

ascents.name: El Chupacabra left
ascents.comment: Pretty cool problem. Loose Cannon ftw!

ascents.name: UCT into Bob's Bulge
ascents.comment: Sliced open my middle finger today, but still managed to three finger this thing. Good old traverses on cloud shadow with the sportiva boyz

ascents.name: Desperate House Boys Traverse
ascents.comment: Really bad problem that I should have flashed but pump/numbed off the top of and almost died. Real men die on traverses. Thanks for grabbing me Purdy!

ascents.name: OG@18 sit
ascents.comment: Can't tell if it's actually difficult or if we were just tired. Weird moves, not so good.

ascents.name: Shaolin Style
ascents.comment: Few goes. Probably not a one move 10. Pretty spectacular location.

ascents.name: Tomahawk Direct
ascents.comment: Not harder than the original and certainly a lot worse. Do the OG first!

ascents.name: Sober Stoner
ascents.comment: Walked past this a million times going by Bierstadt and never tried it, Justin sucked me into another classic. LMK if anyone figures out how this climbs as a 7. The down bump wins again!

ascents.name: Bend and Snap
ascents.comment: Fun climb, weird and shouldery the way I did it. Dihedrals are pretty fun. Right next to Frontrange on Fire

ascents.name: Toxic Shock Low
ascents.comment: First go, but already flashed the stand. Takes 2 stars away from a climb that can't afford to give away that many stars. Go do everything else then come here.

ascents.name: Riddles in the Dark
ascents.comment: Weird and kinda hard. Rough start to the day for Tristan and I. At least I did it. Gonna be desperado from the low.

ascents.name: Sunspot
