ascents.comment: Impossible 4 years ago with bad beta, pretty easy this time around. Rad climb with a rowdy jump, should have used the downwards bump beta on the send to make it sexy.

ascents.name: Never Never Land
ascents.comment: Weirder than it is hard, and certainly a very unattractive boulder. But hey I hiked up here and the movement is good.

ascents.name: Wet Rabbit
ascents.comment: Good movement, pretty easy at my height.

ascents.name: Roundhouse
ascents.comment: Super good. Bullet rock sweet holds and cool movement. Eric's hardest flash!

ascents.name: The Guillotine
ascents.comment: Would be V7 but you actually have to try really hard to keep from dabbing. That was a pitiful warmup boys

ascents.name: Sparrowhawk
ascents.comment: Wow somehow managed a trip dub at lincoln, thought I was tapped out. Although they're all soft and questionable. This problem kind of sucks.

ascents.name: Jimmy's Thang
ascents.comment: Jimmy's soft thang. Jk but I dont know the name so until then. Just right of Guillotine, rad opening moves including a gaston heel toe cam rose move lead to a big huck to the lip -2 feet off the ground classic lincoln. Tuck those knees to your chest for the swing! Great movement.

ascents.name: Zero zero
ascents.comment: Probably my new Go To Grand Wall warmup instead of the contrived summer vacation. Hitting some serious Rampage classics this trip including this and BustedV5. Yes you are seeing that right that is Zero Zero stars BTW.

ascents.name: The reckoning stand
ascents.comment: After all these years it just didn't feel very hard. Must have been really weak 6 years ago. The old "nemesis" goes down!

ascents.name: The Great Escape
ascents.comment: Couple cool moves in a small hole to a tight squeeze out of said small hole. Not very fun honestly but we did it...

ascents.name: One zen
ascents.comment: Been trying this for years don't know what the big deal was... finally pulled it off with Bryce.

ascents.name: Hi Fi
ascents.comment: Small and dumpy but when at Emerald... no other options for a new climb. Epiced on the end could have done it much better. Just had to impress everyone. Ethan flew off spectacularly.

ascents.name: Two Ton Tongue
ascents.comment: Almost pumped out on a 4 move boulder. Consolation prize, topout was fun but a bit chossy. Good thing Josh had my spot.

ascents.name: Mysteries and Insanity
ascents.comment: Beginning was a bit unpleasant, topout was a bit heady, dirty, and questy especially with no pads. Good looking arete though.

ascents.name: Boner Hill
ascents.comment: Didn't know this was actually a thing. Kind of hard definitely unpleasant. Good camaraderie tho!

ascents.name: Eye of the beholder
ascents.comment: EZ with a kneebar. But people are prob taking 11 with a knee pad because they be weak af

ascents.name: Death Cream
ascents.comment: No idea how this thing goes and what's on and off, did a version that felt about as hard as death scream. Contrivances are sick, I'm never coming back to Joe's so sandy.

ascents.name: React to Contact
ascents.comment: Took a bit to figure out, thought it would be impossible from the low when I first climbed it but it gets easier as you learn it.

ascents.name: Replacement Killers
ascents.comment: Fun one, bit of ass slam potential tho. Few tries.

ascents.name: Hard Boiled
ascents.comment: Weird one. Super bad warmup. Not sure where y'all get a knee bar but who kneeds it.

ascents.name: Rhino
ascents.comment: Looked really easy, then felt really hard, then actually was pretty easy. Chris was here but he didn't do it just so everyone knows.

ascents.name: Phish Out of Water
ascents.comment: Not too hard, decent enough though. Mileage day with the crew!

ascents.name: Mandix
ascents.comment: Felt hard but if everyone says it's soft or V9 then I don't want to look weak so it's soft. Really hard tho.

ascents.name: The Donut Thief
ascents.comment: 10 for me. Also nobody else sent so...

ascents.name: The Donut Theif sit
ascents.comment: Prob doesn't add a grade. I guess we started too low on the stand anyways. Similar difficulty, similarly shitty.

ascents.name: Botslayer
ascents.comment: Few goes. Just gotta not be a weenie. Everybody sent!

ascents.name: Arrowhead arete sit
ascents.comment: Almost took me two sessions, wish it would have. Satched it hero burn style end of the session in the dark with Tim. I'll still come back though, what a line. Not freestanding but still really sick. Stand start is pretty stiff for 6... After work seshes! Let's go! Daylight savings!

ascents.name: No Tiempo Moss
ascents.comment: Fun problem, doesn't look the most inspiring though. Not sure how I feel about cliff band bouldering...

ascents.name: Carpet Bombers
ascents.comment: Tired at the end of the day, but glad we came over to see this wall. Cool problem, perfect height!

ascents.name: Channel Incision
ascents.comment: Not my trip for fraishing. Second go soft city!

ascents.name: Nobody
ascents.comment: Jeremy sandbagged my flash to keep me from getting Baba's! Lotsa beta required here. Super fun.

ascents.name: On Location
ascents.comment: Pretty hard for me. Harder than channel incision... big bump beta at the end!

ascents.name: *Outside Logs
ascents.comment: Cool movement and bullet rock on suspiciously sculpted holds. Prob Yosemite V6 but we are in the land of the soft so here it is. Climbed into the stand once from the sit, then did the stand first try.

ascents.name: Banana Slap
ascents.comment: 3rd go. Everything is soft. Rough warm up for sure.

ascents.name: The Distillery
ascents.comment: Really good little 2 mover on bullet. Perfect post vacay boulder, power but not endurance. 3 goes.

ascents.name: Ludacris Extension
ascents.comment: First go. Ludacris into the 8. Link ups for fitness at the end of the day, classic

ascents.name: Qigong
ascents.comment: Managed it without the kneepad. Fun little problem, a bit sharp for sure. Send train for Will and Juli!

ascents.name: Formula 50
ascents.comment: Almost didn't do it, desperate mulligan on last go of the day attempt to finish. Harder than dark waters.

ascents.name: Flight of the Cuckoo
ascents.comment: The one move dyno just left of McMurphy. Start split handed and launch to the top. Good eye Alex! Feels hard and scary until you do it. 8A+ in Africa.

ascents.name: B3PO
ascents.comment: Not a huge fan of traversing but it's ok.

ascents.name: Jacques Cousteau
ascents.comment: 3rd go. Reachy, but a rad one mover nonetheless

ascents.name: Pretentious Vendor of Invention
ascents.comment: Can't wait for that Szechuan sauce

ascents.name: The Dragons Tail
ascents.comment: Gian is close to sending! Cool movement on heinously uncomfortable holds

ascents.name: Macho Man
ascents.comment: Felt hard, but then we started camming and it was soft. Classic dab crux. Finally got a mileage day in.

ascents.name: Tomahawk
ascents.comment: Heel popped immediately on the flash go... whatever I'm not butthurt or anything. Cool feature. Rowland is right, Whispers is for kids. Kids who like climbing better problems than this one. But this is still cool! Made Conor worry about me on the top cuz I was so pumped.

ascents.name: Unshackled Sit
ascents.comment: Well, 3 easy campus moves added on... but considering all of the moves are really easy who can say it doesn't add difficulty? ah well 10 it is.

ascents.name: Tattooed Teardrops
ascents.comment: Fun one that's surprisingly good and not dabby. Nice work Juliet!

ascents.name: Marble direct
ascents.comment: Much sicker but contrived climbing at the top. Eric and Jeremy built the landing up to make it a bit safer. This is what its all about.

ascents.name: Purple Is Not a Color
ascents.comment: Few goes. Hilarious, stupid, fun, and annoying all at the same time.

ascents.name: The Infinite
ascents.comment: Hard for me. But I did do the crimp method in 80 degrees...

ascents.name: Unshackled
ascents.comment: Snow was really high, probably touched a backpack strap. Moves well for a trav, low end.

ascents.name: Honey Badger
ascents.comment: Somehow didn't dab, what a proud line!

ascents.name: Mental Pollution
ascents.comment: What a shitty boulder! Somehow didn't impale my hand. Full foot cut to give the extra split second of time to place my hand safely.

ascents.name: Silverback
ascents.comment: I've done harder V7 lip traverses and never done an easier V10 (or V9) lip traverse but I'll take the quad dub.

ascents.name: Bessie
ascents.comment: A few goes. Sick holds, movement, rock quality... haven't climbed anything like it!

ascents.name: Crimping Matters
ascents.comment: Felt hard to me, but I think I used some bad beta... 1st go already did mind matters.

ascents.name: Center route
ascents.comment: Had to try 150% incredibly difficult for me. Was 75 degrees tho and has been done in tennies so must be soft
A few goes, kinda heinous. Hit the big hold a little low due to an accidental toe hook, and consequently had to do a one hand bump up while barn dooring. Lucky!

ascents.name: Aspen Grove
ascents.comment: Tricky move into the slot. Nice problem! Lotta ways to do this it seems.

ascents.name: Stinkbug
ascents.comment: Did not execute very well but forced it. This is turning into quite a day, trip dub fraish omg

ascents.name: Koyaanisqatsi
ascents.comment: Kinda contrived and a bit chossy but the real detractor is all this grade drama.

ascents.name: The Portal Sit
ascents.comment: Awkward moves into the stand.

ascents.name: Grundel city boys
ascents.comment: Hard for me, also the start hold was wet so climbed it damp... right after the direct.

ascents.name: Purity Control
ascents.comment: Harder than it looks. Got good temps and I'm sure it helped a lot. Pure fosho. Bday send, and a bday punt!

ascents.name: The Nickness
ascents.comment: Wasn't sure which one was easier. I guess this one was. Didn't know what the line was so bailed out the easy slab way. Guess I'll have to do the other top out some other time...

ascents.name: Cage Free
ascents.comment: Nice foot options so all heights can do it. I hate underclings.

ascents.name: Stanley Kubrick
ascents.comment: 3rd go surprisingly long and airy for how little it is.

ascents.name: Pagan Poetry
ascents.comment: After a miserable and wet season in CA the rain tried to stymie my attempts to climb a boulder all the way out here in Utah, but I got one just before the rain. I'm out of shape, and only took a few tries, must be soft.  I'M BACK BITCHES.

ascents.name: Gross's Roof
ascents.comment: I was told this would be easy for me, but when we looked at it in the rain I said it would be hard and everybody laughed. Went back to try and after 2 hours of switching between 6 different betas everyone was still laughing. But I sent finally and it's soft so joke's on you!

ascents.name: Seven Eleven
ascents.comment: Brutal first move for me with the jump, holding the rip is heinous. Wish I was strong enough to campus. Good thing the end is really easy... he said before dry firing off the jug.

ascents.name: Hustle and Flow
ascents.comment: 3 way flash train with Bryce and Mark. Could be easier. Moves really well!

ascents.name: Mega Man
ascents.comment: Easy if you're my height. Fun jump. Muffed the flash, shame on me.

ascents.name: JH
ascents.comment: Pretty cool for a lowball with a double undercling start. So not that cool.

ascents.name: Underworld
ascents.comment: Basically flashed, but dabbed on the swing kinda butthurt but whatever. Did it again dabless yay.

ascents.name: Instinct sit
ascents.comment: Sick line with great movement. Minus a star for death topout or step off, minus a star for glued hold. Rad still!

ascents.name: The White Face
ascents.comment: Cool movement, but kinda unpleasant. Let's get this day started!

ascents.name: Biggie shorty
ascents.comment: So cold can't feel fingers. Both Bryce and my foot slid off on the flash go, so second go soft train it is. Had to force it.

ascents.name: Tres de las quintas
ascents.comment: Blew the flash being weak. Nice ticks for the V0 topout whoever was here last.

ascents.name: Groundhog Day Low
ascents.comment: Brutal. At least this one isn't reachy, right Bryce?

ascents.name: Chattanooga Powerhouse
ascents.comment: Hard for me. Last one to send like always :( shame. shame. SHAME! Forced it.

ascents.name: Osiris
ascents.comment: So good. One of the best of the grade.

ascents.name: Honeycomb
ascents.comment: Really hard for me. Had to go feet first. My back hurts so bad from flying high omg

ascents.name: King James
ascents.comment: 3rd go shame on me. Crimp felt solid, especially because the honker heel holds. Involved.

ascents.name: Slow dance
ascents.comment: Nemesis mega proj for me. Almost did Man-Dance too today after somehow unlocking the moves... Terrible. How has this gotten 3 stars.

ascents.name: Water Hazard
ascents.comment: Took me forever. Tough and really bad.

ascents.name: Bubba Escapes the Ward
ascents.comment: Easy, dunno why I couldn't do it for all these years... get rained out of the milks and this is what it comes to

ascents.name: The Leprechaun Flute
ascents.comment: A few tries. Prime conditions today, and Max took it down too! Solid. I think this one deserves three out of 4 stars.

ascents.name: Supersonic Bionic Robot Voodoo Power
ascents.comment: Few tries. Silly but fun. Chen almost epiced, but wrapped it up just in time. Fell off the top of Atlas a couple times... Nooooo

ascents.name: Once in a While Low
ascents.comment: Max gave it V9 but I don't see a V9 climber ever having a shot at this one so I'm giving it 10. Up from the big bloc by the cool V3 in the hole. 2nd ascent it sounds like...

ascents.name: Fluffy Logic
ascents.comment: So hard for me. But Dylan did it so it's soft. Jumped to the crimp off the 2 finger pocket and campused, it was miserable.

ascents.name: Ride the White Horse
ascents.comment: Hard cuz it's slopers, which means it's actually soft. Fun climbing on nice holds, kinda a battle.

ascents.name: Hydropower (sit)
ascents.comment: Brutal one mover. Took a few tries. pretty miserable. But props to Craig these lowballs are a proper challenge!

ascents.name: Mr. Tricksta
ascents.comment: Maybe the hardest soft 10 I've ever done. 1.5 hours soft. Almost blew my whole day here, on the 2nd problem of the day... Nice vision B Nugs a real gem. If the stand is V8 it's probably actually only V9...

ascents.name: Terrordactyl Sit
ascents.comment: Crimpy, crappy, and easy just how I like it. Yatta boyz train

ascents.name: Cat Daddy
ascents.comment: Bad warmup. EZ with heel jumpless method.

ascents.name: Scarub
ascents.comment: A few tries. Kinda heinous left hand but pretty fun for a one mover!

ascents.name: Stereogram
ascents.comment: Took a few goes. Realized walking up here I blew my flash 4 years ago when I was more of a chuffer than I currently am. Didn't M flash anyways so who cares.

ascents.name: Babies with Rabies
ascents.comment: M flash P flash whatever you wanna call it tried it a long time ago then did it first try today. Pretty nice!

ascents.name: Red cross
ascents.comment: Heinous. Terrible. so unpleasant, but I just want to have a day like Max so here I am.

ascents.name: May it be
ascents.comment: A few tries. Not bad with heel over head beta. Jake's OG beta looks hard. Sit goes... I guess. Finally matched Max's day! I just wanna be like him. 150th double d this year... let's keep it rolling!

ascents.name: Blunt
ascents.comment: So many beta options, eventually ended up with a hybrid of Bryce's and Jake's. Glad to have all this beta!

ascents.name: Truth and Lies
ascents.comment: Thought it would be hard for me but not so bad. Topout is kinda sketch! Oh Joe....

ascents.name: Stumpy Direct
ascents.comment: Uhhh... Super direct is next? The gloves really came way off today. Like way too far off.

ascents.name: Pressure Drop
ascents.comment: Felt like V12, but I know it's not. Hard when it's warm... plus my skin was rolling ;)

ascents.name: White Lines Sit
ascents.comment: Incredibly hard for me, my arms don't function when they are that close together. Didn't start at the super low low sit but Bryce did... still taking it, I almost fell off of every single move.

ascents.name: Something from Nothing
ascents.comment: Few tries. Not so bad, super fun. This boulder is pretty sick...

ascents.name: Hydrocloud
ascents.comment: Just jammed my thumb, and I have bad wrists so the over your head cocked sidepull hold with a key thumbcatch really felt amazing for me. Somehow managed to climb it... and it is cool. Psyched my 200th V10 was originally given V9.

ascents.name: Picture Me Rollin'
ascents.comment: Felt hard a last year but then this C Hoss kid did it so I figured it must be easy. Also I heard he didn't actually do it 2nd go.

ascents.name: Death or Glory
ascents.comment: 1st go soft. Already did ftg and the other link tho so no flash.

ascents.name: Return of the Jedi
ascents.comment: Slogged through the ankle deep marsh to get to this one... wasn't quite worth it but the others rounded out the experience. Pretty cool moves, super lowball and moist.

ascents.name: Skambankt
ascents.comment: Beautiful line out a steep roof that climbs well and isn't dabby. Glad the marsh was worth braving!

ascents.name: Cloverfield
ascents.comment: Wow so soft but also pretty good! Not a fan of these undercling moves...

ascents.name: Slumdog Millionaire
ascents.comment: Really fun line on an amazing boulder out here at Taj Mahal. Glad we made the trip! Bryce had to jump for both the crux moves which I did static... looked really hard and was quite impressive.

ascents.name: Ahab Sit
ascents.comment: Fun jump, kind of hard heel up ass move at the top.

ascents.name: Cry baby
ascents.comment: Fun kneebar climbing, much like Gliding. Mateys kinda sucks though, only downside...

ascents.name: SECTION
ascents.comment: Super long, almost fell off the end... faaaa. Worst I've flashed a climb and still sent.

ascents.name: Poison dwarf direct
ascents.comment: Pretty hard, super shouldery. It was 80 degrees out and in the sun so maybe not hard? moves are kind of cool.

ascents.name: Sangoma
ascents.comment: I think this is the problem I did... couldn't figure out how to pull into the undercling from a sit so I pulled the first move with basically one hand and it felt heinous.

ascents.name: Day of the Jackal
ascents.comment: Quite fun all things considering. Well one thing considering in particular. Well I won't say what that is of course.

ascents.name: Une rime stupide
ascents.comment: Mileage day because I'm only 5 days on, gotta get a workout in.

ascents.name: L'Angelot Incrédule
ascents.comment: Definitely much harder after the break, is what I'm saying while I take 7C+ for this V8

ascents.name: Splash of Red
ascents.comment: Very nice one, climbed it quite shakily but it's a rest day so to be expected.

ascents.name: Ghost In The Darkness
ascents.comment: Took me a long time but it's a personal problem. Definitely physically V7 but I suck.

ascents.name: When the Day Breaks Sit-Start
ascents.comment: Stupid and really hard for me. Worth it? Definitely a hatefuck send. Everyone at Royksopp saw me top this out after much effort... shame on me.

ascents.name: Ron ron et caramel
ascents.comment: Lowball, but as Mark would say, "It's a movement testpiece". Took a while to figure out the beta, and initially I was pretty pissed, but the sequence is quite nice.

ascents.name: Pale Rider
ascents.comment: If you finish left like the book suggests without using the obvious jug right next to the start this thing is seriously fucked. Maybe I was tired at the end of my third day on, maybe it was hot as hell, or maybe y'all are higher than my left nut is over my right and this is sandbagged in both difficulty and quality.

ascents.name: Stretched and Pressed
ascents.comment: Super fun, maybe easier but so is everything so who cares #keeprocklandssoft

ascents.name: Mintberry Crunch
ascents.comment:
Impossible to Soft, a climbing documentary, coming soon to theaters near you.
Also what a dabfest.

ascents.name: Gliding through waves like dolphins
ascents.comment: Should have fraished... Brother B thinks EZ so soft 10 it is. Super fun!

ascents.name: Paula Abdul
ascents.comment: #keeprocklandssoft

ascents.name: Panama
ascents.comment: So bad. And soft.

ascents.name: Pinotage Sit
ascents.comment: Julian with the flash and Will with the FBA! Amazing, nearly perfect rock climb. So psyched.

ascents.name: The shark
ascents.comment: Keep rocklands soft!

ascents.name: The Arc
ascents.comment: 2nd go softing like it ain't no thang. Kinda scary, numbed out on my first go.

ascents.name: Black Mango Chutney
ascents.comment: Sick body positioning on this one. Crimpz

ascents.name: Black Velvet
ascents.comment: Another one I grabbed and then let go of on the flash go... shucks. Easier than hole in one for me. Good first week out here, softies aplenty as promised!

ascents.name: Hole in one
ascents.comment:
Harder than I thought it would be. Most of these dynos feel the same grade...
Julian and Ethan on the follow up!

ascents.name: Flying guitar thief
ascents.comment: Put my hand over the lip and didn't grab on the flash... Well it's rare to get a one two step dyno outside so still psyched! Brian and Brotha B followed, fun to watch the shorter guys fly.

ascents.name: *Macho King
ascents.comment: Sick climb, classic undercling crux. Mark right after on the fraish train!

ascents.name: No Late Tenders
ascents.comment: Fun lowball roof. Lots of power on big holds.

ascents.name: Solar Power
ascents.comment: 3rd go. Kind of annoying to place the kneebar somewhere besides where your hand is, but really fun movement once it works

ascents.name: Berserker
ascents.comment: All of these 10s could be easier out here, but we'll wait on house consensus to pass judgement. Super fun, although contrived. Triple dub frash day whooo!

ascents.name: Kings of convenience
ascents.comment: Harder than Royksopp? Definitely not but took more tries. Like a lot of things here, could be easier.

ascents.name: Caroline
ascents.comment: Shucks. Nice climb, punted the fraish! So many different betas to be had.

ascents.name: Mantra Man
ascents.comment: 1st go. So easy. Like maybe V8. Still taking the pointzzz.

ascents.name: Seamless sit
ascents.comment: Decided to come here instead of Tahoe, and ended up sitting in bumper to bumper traffic for 4 hours and (not) sleeping in a mosquito infested marsh. At least I got to hang with Pinchy and watch him crush!

ascents.name: Love Handles
ascents.comment: Really wanted to take it but I just couldn't. So so so soft even at 10, really adds nothing to climb jugs to this one lock off.

ascents.name: Diamonds are Forever
ascents.comment: Hard for me. Once again had to skip all the holds to make it happen. Scrunchy underclings are my favorite. Blastoff!

ascents.name: Provo Gluru
ascents.comment: 4 sessions, finally figured out the beta and it was definitely soft. Surprised more people don't climb this classic test piece.

ascents.name: Gandhi
ascents.comment: Wow what a really cool uncontrived climb with a pure sit start on comfortable, solid holds. NOT. Sit start at the crimps is wack and stupid (although easy), started at the sloper rail. Still contrived because the jugs out right are off. Also broke a hold on the send. Bryce has the rest...

ascents.name: Hard in the Paint
ascents.comment: Another line with bad rock, but awesome movement on this one. Dyno to finish! Second go soft train with Bryce.

ascents.name: All Thumbs
ascents.comment: Felt like it wasn't going to go and then Isamer got kind of close, and Bryce campused it, and then it felt soft.

ascents.name: Copperhead
ascents.comment: 3rd go. Chris "Copperhead" Chen put in 3 sessions today to no avail. He'll be back for venganza!

ascents.name: Dreamsnatcher
ascents.comment: 3rd go soft. Kicked the tree on the flash go, wussed out from the top 2nd go, and realized it was soft 3rd go. Fairly standard progression for me. Mantle was scary until I did it, and then it too was soft.

ascents.name: Cougar Dyno
ascents.comment: If Dream gets 10 this certainly gets at least as much. Zorro eliminate dyno, good times almost ripping my hand off! Perfect warmup.

ascents.name: Dream
ascents.comment: 4th go soft. Felt very easy for the grade but I need the pointzz

ascents.name: Evilution (to the lip)
ascents.comment: I punted off this 6 years ago so I'll have to take the P Rob flash. Climbed it with the worst beta that exists, but there was such a long line to climb that I didn't want to let go. Nice way to round out a trip dub for the day. Lucid dreaming is next!!!

ascents.name: Left Martini
ascents.comment: Really difficult. Or maybe I'm just fat. Good thing there's a no hands kneebar rest, or I would definitely slide out of a Baby Martini jug.

ascents.name: Full Service
ascents.comment: This is a real v10. So sick.

ascents.name: The Governator
ascents.comment: 3 tries. Easier than predator but I hate underclings.

ascents.name: Predator
ascents.comment: Taking the onsight because I grabbed just about every hold wrong and downclimbed at least a move. Underclings... ewww. At least it's a drop off

ascents.name: Theater of the Absurd
ascents.comment: Spray down from Tomer was an integral part of the Fraish. Still almost fell off at the very end, and the topout was kinda sketchy pumped!

ascents.name: High Scream
ascents.comment: Cool movement, pretty brutal.

ascents.name: Burden of the Beast
ascents.comment: Og non-cheaty beta feels like 10. When on tour...

ascents.name: Focus
ascents.comment: Sick steep climbing on big edges with a spicy topout. Caboose of the send train with c Barthel again. Psyched I finally second go softed something here!

ascents.name: Free Willy
ascents.comment: Straightforward and soft just the way I like it. Choice.

ascents.name: Dean's Journey
ascents.comment: 3rd go, so it must be soft. Actually felt really hard to me, but it's soft. Mostly if gave this 9 I couldn't give it soft so it's 10.

ascents.name: Power of Silence
ascents.comment: Pretty brutal. Almost flashed, fell after going to the finger lock as a sidepull. Realized I should just jump and skip all the holds and followed Conor up. Tag team crushing!

ascents.name: Tequila Sunrise
ascents.comment: Got the spray down from Conor and we both sent. Damn that's fun. Definitely v12, probably upper end. First of many send trains.

ascents.name: Diaphanous Sea
ascents.comment:
Super fun. Felt very low end to me, but harder than Tequila and definitely my style. Quintuple dub day one off to a great start!

Edit: Couldn't keep it at 11, after seeing more stuff here. So soft, can't take the pts. :(

ascents.name: Leo the Lion
ascents.comment: No matter the grade the most rewarding sends are the ones you have to fight for. This is a full value line that never lets up, and climbs like it was set for the World Cup. Ended up in a lot of body positions I have not experienced before en route to the top. Stellar!

ascents.name: Affogato
ascents.comment: The affogat! Been hearing about this boulder for a while. Nice little body tension line with one mildly heinous hold.

ascents.name: Step Child
ascents.comment: Sit to Gym Fag Jiggle. One of the worst problems I have climbed on, and therefore the only one worth mentioning SB south in. Actually I like SB south, except for that Chris Hoss guy, who keeps re-logging climbs to talk smack because he doesn't climb outside anymore. I guess everyone has a different mechanism for coping with being stuck in an organization like OA but come on Chris... this is just sad. Good luck on Bang on this winter!

ascents.name: Where There's a Will There's a Way
ascents.comment: Hardest problem I did today, but only because I couldn't do bunny grinder or global warming. Soft.

ascents.name: Close Encounters of the Turd Kind
ascents.comment: Somehow this was difficult. Oh, and in case anyone was wondering, it does in fact suck.

ascents.name: White Stallion
ascents.comment: 1st try after Soul Glo. This one is good too! Andy and I had a good send training day

ascents.name: Soul Glo
ascents.comment: Everybody fraishes

ascents.name: Shiba Daang
ascents.comment: Harder than Soul Glo, so if that's V10...

ascents.name: Storm Shadow Stand
ascents.comment: Chris Hoss almost did this before me, but then he didn't do it at all. That's what happens when you start talking shit before you send

ascents.name: Whispers of Wisdom
ascents.comment: One of the only problems I've tried here that I'm actually comfortable calling V10. Also one of the only stellar lines, as it is not in a hole. Less than 10 tries, took one epic fall from the slab.

ascents.name: Green 45 Stand
ascents.comment: Since I did well on the stand, it's kind of a no brainer to try the sit... NOT

ascents.name: Skipper Roof Right
ascents.comment: Maybe V10... in Colorado

ascents.name: Mirkwood
ascents.comment: I definitely did not fall off the V1 topout on this one. Ever. How could anyone even think that would be possible.

ascents.name: Phobos
ascents.comment: Had to blow it a couple times before I did it. First move is pretty hard. Wish that dab rock wasn't there.

ascents.name: Tactical Error
ascents.comment: Actually kind of hard. All about body positioning... had to wait til the evening for reasonable temps

ascents.name: Bierstadt
ascents.comment: Felt like 10... ish

ascents.name: Space and Time
ascents.comment: Will is on the comeback train! Fun two mover, def not 3 stars...

ascents.name: Static Reach super low
ascents.comment: Let's get physical

ascents.name: The Real Deal
ascents.comment: Couldn't flash like @theRealHeal, but still pulled it off thanks to his beta.

ascents.name: Pimp slap
ascents.comment: From the sit. Did the top of White Lines so many times today.

ascents.name: Focal Point
ascents.comment: Super weird. Groveled for it...

ascents.name: White Lines Low
ascents.comment: Start at the sit to Pimp Slap, climb into White Lines

ascents.name: Wick's Problem
ascents.comment: Prob 11 if you're short but I'm not

ascents.name: Nazgul
ascents.comment: From one move in. Apparently on this one you can start wherever you want then take a grade. Cool!

ascents.name: Humble Mumble
ascents.comment: Not a big fan of this one

ascents.name: All Or Nothing
ascents.comment: Stupid start into pretty cool v8.

ascents.name: Lumberjack
ascents.comment: My second go game was on today.

ascents.name: Flash Flood
ascents.comment: Nice little compression bloc in the river. Dunno why it felt so hard last time

ascents.name: Diesel Power
ascents.comment: Fraker pissed on it but I think it's hard! Looked down on the big move because I thought I was a goner. 3 pads in the valley... questionable

ascents.name: Rise of the Buddha
ascents.comment: Anything that starts down here gets minus 3 stars

ascents.name: Thong Cave
ascents.comment: Trying hard in a hole. This is rock climbing!

ascents.name: Thriller
ascents.comment: Whaaat didn't think this was going anytime soon. Panicked at the top and flailed through it. Overrated, or maybe I just don't like it cuz it's not soft

ascents.name: Pine Box
ascents.comment: Amazing feature. Josh and I got it done real quick... on that real shit.

ascents.name: Cilley
ascents.comment: Moves well, kinda sharp though. Thumb lead to shoulder explosion, so sick.

ascents.name: Delta V
ascents.comment:
I'll Delta your V

grade

ascents.name: Wall to Wall Carpet SDS
ascents.comment: Really wanted to flash so I could make a comment about having tried it 7 years ago. Very difficult for me, but it's a personal problem

ascents.name: Good Vibrations
ascents.comment: Mor-pho-logical

ascents.name: Across the Tracks
ascents.comment: After much discussion with Will, I give this a qualified thumbs up. Great line!

ascents.name: Orange Fever
ascents.comment: Capped off my coming up day in the valley. Finally achieved the big 100. Low moves suck, stand start is rad. Happy isles may be the sickest sector in the world.

ascents.name: Bubba gump
ascents.comment: Impossible for the longest time, but turns out it was soft

ascents.name: Stand and deliver
ascents.comment: Looks a lot harder if you are short. What a line... 5 goes, but who's counting

ascents.name: Americana exotica
ascents.comment: 5 sessions. Brutal nemesis for me, underclings are not my game. Might be 9 for some but not Fanny. The first problem I wanted to do in Red Rocks.

ascents.name: Progressive Guy
ascents.comment: Pretty close to redlining this thing. Battletoads taught me a lot about how to do this type of problem, really felt like I learned a lot from both problems

ascents.name: Skidmark
ascents.comment: Good style match for me. Crux hold was eroding in my hand, wish it was better rock

ascents.name: Battletoads
ascents.comment: 3 Sessions. Send was inspired by Bryce's comment. Warpath is next.

ascents.name: Jitterbug Perfume
ascents.comment: Picture 4 dudes mummying all their tips with tape in the freezing cold, not having any fun. Almost punted too...

ascents.name: Milkman Sit
ascents.comment: Brutally pumpy. Climbs well except for the tree and the weird landing

ascents.name: Black Dahlia
ascents.comment: I love Black D. Feels like one of the stiffest 10s I've gotten on

ascents.name: Superman
ascents.comment: Send train with Bryce. Stellar line, 3 sketchy punchy moves over the lip make it exciting.

ascents.name: Span Man
ascents.comment: Couldn't do the heel without feeling like I would get injured. Had to invoke Okham's Razor and just try really hard

ascents.name: Trickle of Silence
ascents.comment: Tag team with Bryce after we got wrecked first sesh. Hard til it's easy

ascents.name: Chutzpah
ascents.comment: Booty so smooth can't believe it's not butter

ascents.name: The peephole
ascents.comment: This thing is brutal. Felt like a fluke, but somehow it went in one session. My shoulder...

ascents.name: Superman
ascents.comment: Glad Max pointed this thing out or I might not have tried it! Cool line, superbumped and campused my feet out.

ascents.name: Cotton pony
ascents.comment: Felt pretty hard to get my weight onto that sick pinch properly. Sticking that move from the sit looks nuts.

ascents.name: The Practitioner
ascents.comment: Probably could have flashed... but finished in a few goes after some beta refinements. Had to retro DG so Scott could be first

ascents.name: The Seam
ascents.comment: Thought this was super hard and couldn't do it 3 years in a row but now that I did... didn't feel so bad

ascents.name: Welcome to the Darkside
ascents.comment: If you're tall it could be as easy as 9. If you're short... 12? Either way, awesome problem with great movement. Wish the top was a little cleaner, thought I was going to rip something off for sure. 3 stars but it's qualified because the rock quality is iffy in some places.

ascents.name: Tour de France Center Right
ascents.comment: more qualified variations. spending a lot of time at this boulder...

ascents.name: DRM
ascents.comment: Felt hard the first day I tried it, tweaked the beta a bit and it felt easy... not sure on the grade here

ascents.name: The Onion
ascents.comment: two stars for the crazy moves. looked impossible, but with bicycles and a 6 foot wing span it isn't too bad

ascents.name: Chupamihuevos sit start
ascents.comment: feels pretty hard, could have been the heat tho. couple cool intro moves to add uncertainty to the hard move. kinda like a lesser version of the egg in squammy

ascents.name: Shake 'n' Bake
ascents.comment: used an easier sequence than the original cutting left a bit lower. still pretty hard

ascents.name: It's Not My Trash
ascents.comment: Cool moves, but really sharp and lowball. Must have used some different beta than other peoples cause it went down as soon as I yelled timber... felt about v10

ascents.name: Lindner Problem
ascents.comment: Great problem in a weird spot. Kinda heady at the top, psyched on this one!

ascents.name: Danimal
ascents.comment: Might be the hardest move I've done. Couldn't keep any feet on so I jumped...

ascents.name: Beat me off Scottie
ascents.comment: Could be easier... Such a cool problem! Chen said he wasn't close then sent first try
